title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherry pie filling or pineapple, cake mix and coconut in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and pour over all the ingredients. Over this, sprinkle the chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mint chip pie
directions: Spread softened ice cream into the crust.
Freeze 2 hours. In saucepan, combine sugar, butter, chocolate and milk.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until thick.
Let cool.
Spoon over pie. Chill.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, salt and spices in a pan; set aside.
Stir once in a while.
While you prepare vegetables, mix good and place in large mouth gallon jar.
Pour vinegar mixture over pickles and put in icebox.
Stir pickles every day or two; best after 2 weeks.

title: old fashioned light fruit cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamed.
Add eggs, one at the time, beating after each addition until yolk is broken.
Then add flavoring.
Sift flour, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon together.
Add to sugar mixture gradually.
Work in nuts and fruit with a heavy spoon.
Pour into prepared pans filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 275°, tube pan about 3 hours, 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans about 2 hours.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Beat in sugar and salt.
Stir in other ingredients.
Freeze in electric churn until firm.
Serve.

title: diet lasagna
directions: Cook tomato sauce 30 minutes slowly.
Meanwhile, stir-fry onions, green pepper and celery in pan.
Fry ground meat separately.
When done, mix oil together.
Have cooked lasagna ready.
No eggs, no cheese, use other seasonings if wish.
Makes 1 or 2 layers depending on the size of pan.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: marinade sauce(best on london broil)
directions: Marinate at least 4 hours.

title: norwegian almond cookies
directions: Mix and set aside 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons finely ground almonds. In bowl, cream the butter, salt and powdered sugar, about 10 minutes. Mix in the ground almonds. Stir in the lemon juice and almond flavoring. Add the flour and mix well. Roll into small balls, then roll them into the sugar and almonds mixture that was set aside. Press each ball flat with a glass on greased sheet or use parchment paper. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Prepare peaches.
Mix with 1 cup of sugar.
Set oven at 350°. Put margarine into 2 1/2 x 3-inch deep casserole and set in oven to melt.
In another bowl, stir 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir. Put sugared peaches on top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together until crumbly.
Mix vinegar, egg and water together.
Add to first mixture.
Work into a ball. Refrigerate for 1 hour before rolling into pie shells.
This will keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Can also be frozen.
Makes 5 or 6 pie shells.

title: pumpkin rolls (bread)
directions: Mix well the first 5 ingredients.
Then add pumpkin, powdered milk and egg.
Beat well.
Stir into 4 to 5 cups unsifted flour. Mix well, knead well and let rise until double.
Roll to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter or make in any desired manner for rolls.
Let rise until double.
Bake about 30 minutes at 375°.

title: venison patties
directions: Put venison, bacon and onion through grinder.
Mix well and add egg and seasonings.
Form into patties.
Roll in flour or bread crumbs and fry.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: Steam squash and onion in a saucepan until tender; drain.
Add stuffing mix, milk, eggs and cheese; mix well.
Spoon into lightly oiled baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: clinton cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a
medium bowl, combine oats, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into balls about 1 1/2-inch round (with hands).
Roll each ball into powdered sugar and place in candy papers for serving on cookie platter.

title: cheddar fish bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients except fish.
Mix well.
Stir in fish.
Place mixture in 1-quart baking dish that has been sprayed with non-stick cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: frosty fruit salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water and dissolve over hot water; add to mayonnaise.
Whip the cream until stiff and fold into mixture. Add fruit and nuts, folding in carefully.
Pour into a mold or molds and refrigerate approximately 4 hours before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake 30 minutes at 350° or use crock-pot.

title: gnocchi
directions: In bowl, pour boiling water over Potato Buds.
Mix well.
Let cool.
Add flour and baking powder; mix to form ball.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Roll on floured board to form a 3/4-inch thick rope. Cut into 3/4-inch pieces.
Roll each against fork, making indentation with thumb.
Drop in boiling water (add a little oil) and boil 1 minute.
Gnocchi will come to top.
Drain and serve with melted butter and grated cheese or with your favorite spaghetti sauce and cheese.
Gnocchi can be frozen.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Slice bananas and line pie crust.
Mix banana pudding as directed.
Add remaining banana slices.
Then mix in half of Cool Whip.
Spread evenly into pie crust.
Add the remaining Cool Whip to the top and spread evenly.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and water.
Add pudding mix, beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well. Combine flour, salt and soda; add eggs to mixture.
Add vanilla, coconut, dates, apples and nuts.
Batter will be thick.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Thaw soup; mix with shrimp and cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix pumpkin filling as directed on the can.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour filling into cake pan.
Take white cake mix and sprinkle over filling; mix into pumpkin filling. Slice margarine over everything.

title: spinach and cheese appetizers
directions: Squeeze thawed spinach to extract liquid.
When spinach is dry, place in a large bowl and add bread crumbs, eggs, butter, onion, cheeses and garlic.
Blend well.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 50 appetizers.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Melt chocolate with water over very low heat, stirring until smooth.
Add 1/2 c. sugar, cook and stir 2 minutes.
Cool.	Mix flour with 1 1/4 c. sugar, baking soda and salt.
Beat margarine in a large bowl, beat in flour and chocolate mixtures, eggs, milk and vanilla until blended.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, remove, cool on racks.
Split, making 4 layers. Place one layer on plate, spread 1 cup of the chocolate filling over cake.	Repeat layers.	(If filling thickens, add about 1 Tbsp. milk.)
Chill about 1 hour.
Garnish with 1 1/4 c. thawed Cool Whip and chocolate curls.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Form into 1-inch diameter balls. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 150 small balls.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Mix in 1 to 2 tablespoons water to moisten. Pat into an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Top with catsup, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain off fat.
Add soups, milk, chiles, olives and salt.
Mix.
Layer tortillas, meat mixture and cheese.
Layer these until all is used, ending with cheese (in large casserole).
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: raisin scones
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in butter and shortening.
Add raisins.
Beat the egg in a 8 ounce measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 1 cup liquid.
Add to flour mixture and mix to make a soft dough.
Divide dough in half.
Place each half on lightly floured board.
Pat out into 1 thick circle.
Cut into 6 triangles and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
This freezes well and a few seconds in the microwave oven and they taste fresh.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Blend with spoon or use blender.
Chill and serve.
Will keep 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.
Makes 4 cups.

title: boiled shrimp
directions: Put lemon and onion into bag with crab boil.
Add salt and bag of seasonings to water.
Bring to boil.
Add shrimp and bring back to boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove shrimp and drain.
Perfect shrimp every time.

title: spaghetti (chicken)
directions: Brown pepper, onion and mushrooms in butter.
Put boned chicken breast in baking dish.
Put cheese on top of chicken. Stir pepper, onion and mushrooms into spaghetti sauce.
Cover chicken and cheese with sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: marie hardegree's jumbo stuffed shells
directions: Brown meat.
Drain on paper towel.
In separate pan, saute onion in oil.
Add 1/2 cup cheese, meat, garlic and enough sauce to cover meat.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Cook shells according to package directions.
Stuff shells with meat.
Arrange in a baking dish.
Cover with remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fudge cakes
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and pecans.
Melt chocolate and margarine together.
Add flour and sugar mixture to eggs, then add chocolate mixture, vanilla and pecans.
Bake in cupcake papers 30 minutes at 325°.

title: cranberry orange with cherry gelatin
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in Indian Trail cranberry orange sauce and pineapple.
Pour into mold.

title: australian meat pie
directions: Remove all fat from steak and cut steak into 1/2 inch cubes. Heat oil in a large saucepan and fry steak in small lots until browned.
Set aside.
Fry onion until browned, add celery and carrot and cook a few minutes, stir-fry fashion.
Return meat to saucepan; add stock, cover and simmer gently for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and nutmeg and simmer for a further 30 minutes, until meat is cooked.
Blend soy sauce, flour and a little water to make a smooth paste.
Stir into saucepan; allow to thicken.
Taste and adjust flavor if required.
Allow to cool while rolling out pastry.

title: anne-marie's strawberry salad
directions: Heat strawberry juice and water to make 1 1/4 cups.
Dissolve Jell-O in liquid and ice cream and stir until dissolved.
Chill until firm, but not set.
Fold in strawberries.
Chill.
This can be made using raspberry Jell-O and frozen raspberries.

title: tamale pie
directions: Fry beef until nearly done.
Add onion and garlic.
Fry until onion is soft.
Stir flour, chili powder, salt and pepper into meat mixture.
Add tomatoes, chili sauce and ripe olives.
Simmer until blended.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Mix together with hands. Blend in garlic and nuts.
Shape into rolls.
Sprinkle chili mix on foil.
Roll cheese roll in chili mix.
Wrap in foil and place in refrigerator.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1/4 cup margarine until tender.
Combine onion, soup, mushrooms, cheese, parsley, salt, pepper, almonds and broccoli; mix well.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole.

title: foil dinner for 1
directions: Tightly wrap in foil with meat on bottom and vegetables on top.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook over coals 30 to 45 minutes, turning often, or, cook in box oven for 45 to 60 minutes without turning.

title: almond crab dip
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: wesley punch
directions: Chill juices.
Let frozen juices thaw in refrigerator.
Don't chill 7-Up.
Mix the juice first, then Southern Comfort, then the 7-Up.

title: cream of fennel soup
directions: Trim and wash the fennel.
Cut in into quarters and cook it in boiling salted water with lemon juice until tender (30 minutes). Drain and roughly slice fennel.
Melt butter in a large saucepan and saute the fennel in it for a few minutes.
Stir in the flour, then add half the stock, milk, mace, seasoning and parsley.
Puree the soup.
Pour the soup back into the saucepan, add the remaining stock and milk and bring to a boil.
Simmer gently, stirring occasionally, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot garnished with chopped parsley and fennel sprig.
Serves 4.

title: poor man's steak
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Pat mixture on a cookie sheet.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 6 squares, roll each square in flour and brown in large skillet coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Yields 6; each serving contains 388 calories (53% from fat).

title: italian fondue
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Sprinkle packaged sauce over meat.
Add tomato sauce, cheeses, cornstarch and wines (in that order).
Stir over medium heat while cheese is melting.
Serve in fondue type pot with French bread or sourdough bread.

title: no-roll sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, white and 10x sugar.
Beat together well beaten eggs and salt; add to butter and sugar.
Stir in oil and vanilla. Sift flour, baking soda and cream of tartar and stir into mixture. With small spoon take piece of dough about walnut size.
Roll in hands to form ball.

Place 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet. Lightly grease bottom of glass tumbler 2 1/2 inches in diameter. Dip glass in white or colored sugar and press dough balls flat. Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes. Makes 1 dozen 2 inch cookies.

title: peach pie filling salad
directions: Drain canned fruit. Add to pie filling. Add marshmallows and sliced bananas. Chill until ready to serve.

title: bubble bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Place frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with pecans, brown sugar and dry butterscotch pudding.
Melt oleo and pour over rolls.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Let rise overnight.
Remove aluminum foil.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Turn out on plate.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into bite size balls.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be frozen and served later.

title: onion roasted mashed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In large bag, add all ingredients, except milk. Close bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, arrange potatoes. Discard bag. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Turn potatoes into large bowl. Mash potatoes and stir in hot milk.

title: quick and easy peach dessert
directions: In baking pan, place 3/4 box of cake mix on the bottom.
Slice 6 slices of margarine and layer on mix.
Combine peaches and cinnamon on top of mix.
Place remaining cake mix over peaches. Slice butter and lay on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake until golden brown.

title: keepsake biscuits
directions: Knead well and mold into neat small biscuits with your hands. Bake well and you have good sweet biscuits that will keep for weeks in a dry place.
Great for traveling.

title: nana's crumb cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour 4 (8-inch) pie pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Immediately brush with butter and sprinkle lightly with sugar upon removing from oven.

title: appetizer salmon ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients except parsley.
Shape mixture into a ball.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Coat ball with parsley.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: baby food pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt butter.
Add to graham cracker crumbs with 1/2 cup of sugar mixed in it.
Whip cream cheese until smooth (add 1 cup of milk gradually to help blend), then add 1 cup sugar and 2 packages Dream Whip until blended.
Then layer:
first layer, graham crackers; second layer, cream cheese mix; third layer, cherries. Continue until all used up.
Chill for about 3 to 4 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Prepare instant pudding as directed on package.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 X 13 dish.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: shrimp and pistachio spread
directions: Place cottage cheese, lemon juice and onion powder in blender or food processor.
Cover and blend on high speed about 2 minutes, stopping blender occasionally to scrape sides, or process 30 seconds or until smooth.
Pour into small bowl.
Stir in shrimp and nuts.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve with assorted crackers or ruffled potato chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels, milk and butter over low heat.
Set aside.
Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan which has been greased.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread caramel mixture on top. Sprinkle nuts and chips on caramel mixture.
Pour remaining batter on top and return to oven.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
You can use milk chocolate chips instead of semi-sweet chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: new potatoes and peas
directions: Wash and scrape or peel potatoes.
Place in saucepan with potatoes only half covered in water.
Salt and cover.
Cook 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain, saving 1/2 cup stock.
Melt margarine.
Blend in flour.
Cook about 1/2 minute.
Pour potato cooking water into 2-cup measuring cup and finish filling with milk.
Add butter and flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir and cook until thickens.
Add salt, basil and pepper.
Add to cooked potatoes.
Add peas.
Heat 1 to 2 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheesecake brownies
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan. Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cake mix, margarine and beaten egg together.
Forms cookie dough texture. Spread with hands across bottom of pan.
Beat confectioners sugar, cream cheese and eggs until well mixed.
Pour over cake mixture and bake 50 minutes at 325°.
Cut in small squares.

title: tammy (schen) fields oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugars and eggs together.
Then add flour mixture. Add oatmeal and mix together well.
Add chocolate chips.
Put out by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix
half
of the flour (4 cups) and all other ingredients for
minutes.
Stir
in	remaining
flour;
mix well. Shape
in 1	large
ball
and let rise until doubled in size. Punch	down; let
rise again.
After second rising, roll out. Cut
into biscuit
size.
Dip in melted butter.
Put in pans. Let rise once more.
Bake at 350° to 400° until brown.

title: treet salad
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Can be used as a salad or as a sandwich filling.

title: 24 salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in a large casserole that can be covered tightly.
Spread or pat mayonnaise smoothly on top after all layers are laid.
Mix 1
teaspoon sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Sprinkle over mayonnaise.
Top with mixture of mayonnaise and cheese.
Cover tightly and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Slice to serve.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp tomato drink
directions: Blend and chill 24 hours.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.
This is good served with cheese and crackers.

title: brown rice
directions: In 1/2-quart casserole layer first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: heavenly corn pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole or pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach-cucumber salad
directions: Thinly slice unpared cucumber into bowl.
Pour salad dressing over slices; cover and refrigerate.
Wash spinach and remove stems; dry leaves.
Into salad bowl, tear greens into bite size pieces.
Pour cucumber slices with dressing over spinach.
Add peanuts and toss.
Makes 8 servings.

title: so easy barbecue
directions: Fry hamburgers and onions until done.
Mix ketchup, water, and flour.
Add to hamburger and onions.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve on buns.
Serves 4-6 depending on bun size.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Cream milk and lemon juice with beaters.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: About 2 hours before serving or a day ahead, in small bowl, combine walnuts, cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar.
Grease 10-inch tube pan.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat butter or margarine with 1 1/4 cups sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and remaining ingredients and beat at low speed until blended, constantly scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Increase speed to medium; beat 3 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread half of batter in pan; sprinkle with half of nut mixture and spread evenly with remaining batter and sprinkle with remaining nut mixture.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool cake in pan completely on wire rack. Makes 12 servings.
Enjoy!
It's delicious!

title: boat dip
directions: Mix and stir.
Make one day ahead.
On day of use, hollow out bread (pumpernickel or rye) and fill with the dip made the previous day.
Use the chunks out of the bread for the dipping.

title: pecan fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, milk and pecans.
Cook slowly until firm balls form in water (it will turn a dark color).
Remove from heat.
Add a little vanilla extract and margarine. Whip mixture until thick.
Pour into greased dish. Cool and cut into squares.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place
popped
corn
and
nuts in large paper bag.
Set aside. Put
brown
sugar,
butter,
corn
syrup and salt in 2 quart glass
bowl.
Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes, stirring after each minute, until it boils.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Stir in baking soda.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and form into rolls.
Let set in cold place overnight. Slice into thin slices.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in moderate oven.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and enjoy!

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Spread berries in pan and top with pineapple.
Pour cake mix over berries and pineapple, then add the nuts.
Cut the oleo and generously cover all over the top.
Sprinkle with sugar (optional).
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° until top is lightly browned and bubbling.

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix
all
together.
Refrigerate dough several hours or overnight.	Make
into
small balls; put on cookie sheet lined with foil.	Place them about 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 6 to	8
minutes.
Remove
cookies
on foil and let them cool. Then peel foil off.
Use new foil for each pan of cookies.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add cranberry sauce, beating well. Stir in 3 cups water and pineapple juice.
Heat to serving temperature.
Serve immediately.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix together and drop on hot griddle.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water.
Mash as you usually do.
Mix in all other ingredients; beat until well blended.
Cool and store in covered container in refrigerator.
To heat, place desired amount in casserole.
Spread with margarine and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
(These potatoes will keep for 2 weeks in the refrigerator.)

title: easy bread and rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour, oil, sugar, salt and egg.
Beat with electric mixer for 3 minutes.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Add remaining flour and knead until elastic and smooth (10 minutes).
Let rise until doubled in bulk and shape into 2 large loaves or 4 dozen rolls.
Bake at 350° to 375°.
I make cinnamon rolls.

title: canadian vanilla syrup
directions: Bring ingredients to a full boil (frothy).
Delicious especially on waffles.

title: whipped jello pudding(heritage)
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions on box.
Refrigerate until Jell-O just begins to congeal.
Whip cream.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Put a layer of Jell-O in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; then add a layer of vanilla wafers, followed by a layer of whipped cream.
Repeat layers, ending with whipped cream on top.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add brown sugar.
Cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and cook and stir until comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool about 10 minutes.
Then add confectioners sugar, beating well, until cool enough to spread.

title: crispy oven fried okra
directions: Wash okra.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper in bowl.
Stir well.
Set aside.
Combine buttermilk and egg in large bowl.
Stir in okra.
Let stand 10 minutes. Dredge okra in cornmeal.
Place okra on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes or until crisp.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: In bowl, beat together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until fluffy. Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Add pumpkin mixture.
Mix thoroughly and spread in a 15x10 greased pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool then frost.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix in order given. Divide batter into 3 bread pans, greased and floured bottoms only. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Saute onion in small amount of cooking oil.
Add ground beef and brown; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.

title: rock cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by 1/2 to 1 teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for about 15 minutes.

title: four hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water. Let this stand in cup while mixing the rest.

title: pumpkin spice bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottom and sides of 15 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan lightly with shortening. Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin in large bowl until smooth. Stir in flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, ginger and cloves. Spread in prepared pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until light brown. Cool completely in pan on wire rack. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting* and top with walnuts. Cut into 2 x 1/2-inch bars. Refrigerate any leftover bars.

title: low-fat snow peas oriental
directions: Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Add oil; place over medium heat until hot.
Add snow peas and carrots.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Add chestnuts and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Combine soy sauce and cornstarch, stirring until cornstarch is dissolved.
Add to vegetable mix.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Serve immediately.
About 51 calories per 1/2-cup serving.

title: shorties
directions: Cream margarine; stir in flour and nuts.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Shape into small balls and bake in a 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until slightly brown.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool before serving.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash tomatoes and cut off stem ends. Cut the tomatoes in half crosswise.
Sprinkle them with salt and pepper.
Mix the bread crumbs, parsley and oil together in a small bowl.
Spread each tomato half with bread crumbs mixture.
Place tomatoes in greased baking dish.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until bread crumbs are golden brown.

title: saute of two squashes
directions: Wash squash and zucchini under cold running water.
Trim stem and blossom ends off.
Cut in 2-inch lengths.
Cut each piece lengthwise into 1/2-inch slices.
Stack slices and cut into 1/2-inch julienne strips.
Heat butter until foamy in large skillet over medium heat.
Add squash and toss until coated with butter.
Saute, tossing, until crisp and tender, about 4 minutes. Increase heat to high.
Sprinkle with thyme, salt and pepper. Cook, tossing, until squash is lightly browned, about 2 minutes. Note:
One fourth teaspoon dried thyme may be substituted for the fresh.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Brown sirloin in oil.
Add vegetables.
Mix gravy mix, water and soy sauce together.
Add spices.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Simmer 1 minute until thickened.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: cantaloupe pie
directions: Dice cantaloupe; cook in small amount of water until tender. Drain and measure.
Combine remaining ingredients in double boiler; add cantaloupe and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shells and top with meringue.
Brown in hot oven.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese, soft butter, salt, chicken and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Separate rolls, spread 1/4 cup mixture on each.
Roll up, starting with the short side of the triangle. Roll to opposite point, tuck side and point under to seal.
Dip in melted butter, then in the corn flake crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet; bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Serve with Sour Cream Gravy.

title: shrimply great mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water and set aside.
In a saucepan, heat soup.
Add gelatin mixture and stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese, remove from heat and beat until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a well oiled mold and chill until firm.
Serve slices over
crisp lettuce leaf or serve with crackers on the buffet table.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and shape into balls, placing in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Place chicken halves in glass dish.
Mix together lime and pineapple juices and minced garlic.
Pour over chicken; turn to coat all sides.
Marinate about 30 minutes.
Remove chicken from marinade; season with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Brush lightly with oil and grill over medium heat, cook until chicken is done. Remove from grill and slice in thin strips.
Serve chicken piled in hot flour tortillas.
Spread with guacamole and top with salsa. Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican style meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Shape into loaf. Spray pan with Pam. Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until beef is no longer pink.

title: spaghetti sauce for a crowd
directions: Puree tomatoes, onions and garlic in blender.
Pour into very large saucepan.
Add tomato paste, sugar, salt, oregano and oil. If using meat, place in very large frying pan and cook until light brown.
Drain excess fat and add bell peppers that have been cut up in small pieces.
Also, add Worcestershire sauce and black pepper.
Add to tomato sauce and place in a commercial size or 5 gallon saucepan.
Mix well and simmer for 1 to 3 hours with or without the meat.
Yield:
200 servings.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix with a spoon (don't use a mixer) just until mixed well. Spread into an ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar, or make a powdered sugar frosting using lemon juice for the liquid.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix in cornmeal, oil, onions, peppers and corn.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes in oblong pan.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Bring to a boil and boil for approximately 5 minutes.

title: russian salad
directions: In a sauce pan dissolve jello in boiling water, then add marshmallows and stir until dissolved on low heat.
Add the rest of the ingredients and put in refrigerator.
Serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: crabmeat surprise
directions: Mix 1/2 can soup with meat and broccoli.
Cover with stuffing. Top with remaining soup and cheese.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour. (Can be fixed in advance and frozen until ready to use.)

title: tiramisu
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar and wine in a bowl.
Cook this mixture in a double boiler for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Now mix the Mascarpone cheese with the egg mixture until smooth.
(You can add some of the coffee to help it become thinner.)
Quickly dip the ladyfingers in the Espresso and one by one place them uniformly in a casserole dish.
Spread a layer of cheese mixture on top of ladyfingers.
Add another layer of ladyfingers on top of cheese mixture, then add another layer of cheese mixture.
Repeat process. End with last layer being the cheese mixture and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Sprinkle with cocoa powder and serve.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix thawed strawberries with the milk, Cool Whip and bananas. Freeze and serve when hard.

title: party wieners
directions: Mix jelly and barbecue sauce.
Add wieners.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mustard ring maxwell(san francisco)
directions: Beat eggs in top of double boiler.
Mix together thoroughly the sugar and gelatin.
Stir in the mustard, turmeric and salt. Add the water until slightly thickened, stirring continuously. Cool until it is thick; whip the cream and stir in.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
Fill center with cole slaw, pineapple, red onion rings or whatever.
You will love it.

title: creamy potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Transfer to ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until heated through. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the oil and sugar thoroughly.
Add the eggs, milk and bananas.
Stir in the flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: honey chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pepper chicken and place in large baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients; pour over chicken. Bake for 1 hour.
Sauce will be thick.

title: easy ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Place Tater Tots in casserole dish (can thaw in microwave until Tater Tots are soft).
Mash Tater Tots with potato masher or fork.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, sour cream and milk together and pour over Tater Tots.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top and mix slightly into potatoes along with small ham pieces.
Dot top of mixture with margarine and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
If mixture seems too dry, add extra milk. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour to 40 minutes.
Done when slightly golden brown. This is an excellent covered dish.

title: barbecued potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In Dutch oven over medium heat, bring water, barbecue sauce, vinegar, salt and pepper to boil.
Stir in potatoes and onion.
Simmer 5 minutes; stir occasionally.
Cover and bake 1 hour or until tender.
Serve hot or cold, garnished with paprika and parsley.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In an extra large mixing bowl, mix the first 4 ingredients. Cool until lukewarm.
Add beaten eggs.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onions, water and salt until potatoes are tender.
Mash with a potato masher in the water they are cooked in. Add evaporated milk, corn and butter.
Heat (do not boil) and serve.

title: corn fritters(amish)
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Beat egg yolks, flour, baking powder, salt, pepper, milk and sugar and add to the grated corn.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in egg whites.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased frying pan.
Turn when golden brown on bottom, then brown top.
Serve warm with syrup.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: While broccoli is thawing in 1 cup boiling salted water, saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add soup and milk. Simmer about 3 minutes. Add Cheez Whiz.
Mix well. Add broccoli and rice.
Add seasoning and slivered almonds.
Put in buttered casserole dish and bake for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: kibbeh(ground lamb and burghul)
directions: Food Grinder Method:
Place burghul in a bowl, cover with cold water and leave to soak for 10 minutes.
Drain in a sieve and press with back of spoon to remove as much moisture as possible. Tip into a flat dish, spread out and chill in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours.
This also dries it further.
Trim all fat and fine skin from meat and cut into cubes.
Chill for 1 hour, if not very cold.
Pass meat through grinder twice, using fine screen.
Grind onion twice and combine with meat, burghul, salt, pepper and allspice.
Pass through grinder twice, adding a little iced water or ice chips, if mixture feels warm.
Knead to a smooth, light paste with hands, adding iced water or ice chips when necessary. Cover and chill until required.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until lightly brown.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Press ground beef into the bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread soup evenly over top of meat.
Lay Tater Tots on top; bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: ornaments
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water all at once and stir until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until consistency of cookie dough.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Paint with tube or bright water colors.
If dough starts to dry out, wet hands and work the dough.

title: creamy crab dip
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a small bowl and stir well. Stir in crabmeat.
Transfer mixture to a serving bowl.
Serve with Melba rounds or fresh raw vegetables.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: creole shrimp
directions: Heat oil in skillet (I use electric).
Add garlic and onion. Cook until almost transparent, then add green pepper and cook until transparent.
Add tomatoes, bay leaves, hot sauce or cayenne pepper, salt and pepper and chili powder.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
About 20 minutes before serving, add chopped celery and cook until almost looses its crispness.
Add shrimp.
Simmer until shrimp has warmed.
Serve over hot rice.

title: italian garden saute
directions: Saute all ingredients, except tomatoes, in butter.
When vegetables are tender, stir in tomatoes and heat through.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Spread in ungreased baking dish.
Layer ham and cheese over broccoli.

title: "moose's" p.j.
directions: Cut lemons, limes and oranges into half moons.
Put in cooler. Add Everclear or vodka and cherries.
Add juicy red punch and cherries.
Add Welch's grape juice concentrate, mix well; taste. Add Sprite or Sun Drop if needed.
This recipe may be doubled or tripled for larger yields.

title: nut brownies
directions: Blend sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix well. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle cooled brownies with confectioners sugar or spread with cocoa frosting.

title: stuffed crab
directions: Mix bread crumbs, milk and eggs; set aside.
In a skillet, saute butter, onion, green onion, bell pepper and garlic.
When soft, add crabmeat, salt and pepper (to taste) and continue to saute.
Add a dash of Worcestershire sauce and bread crumb mixture.
Mix well and cook on low fire until light brown.
Stir often to prevent sticking.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles.
Soften butter and cream cheese over low heat. Put sugar in large bowl.
Throw on hot, drained noodles and mix well.
Add cream cheese mixture; mix well.
Add sour cream, eggs and vanilla; mix all together.
Put into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. May be cut in half.

title: crab cakes
directions: Empty crab meat into large mixing bowl.
Mix with a fork the other ingredients in the order given.
Form into 10 crab balls or cakes.
Use more mayonnaise or salad dressing if necessary to hold cakes together.
Fry in oil until brown on each side.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Add 1 cup of water to 2 cups of raisins and boil 5 minutes. Cool.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, nutmeats and raisins.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: round steak
directions: Cut steak into 5 or 6 pieces.
Place in slow cooker.
Add dry ingredients, water and soup.
Cover and cook on low for 5 or 6 hours or longer if needed.
Serve with mashed potatoes.
Yields 5 or 6 servings.

title: popeye's pita bites
directions: Combine spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, green onions, soup mix and water chestnuts in bowl.
Mix well.
Fill pita rounds just before serving.
Makes 10 servings.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Boil potatoes whole.
Cut into slices 1/4 inch thick.
Set aside.
Melt cheese and butter in sauce pan on top of stove.
Add onion, sour cream, salt, and pepper to cheese mixture.
Mix in Potatoes.
Place in a large baking dish and cook for 45 minutes.

title: salsa pronto
directions: Place tomatoes in blender, one can at a time.
Cover and run on lowest speed 2 seconds to chop tomatoes.
In bowl, combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Makes 4 cups.

title: coleslaw souffle salad
directions: In a large mixer bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in mayonnaise, vinegar, water and salt.
Chill until partially set.
It should be the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Beat with an electric mixer on medium speed until fluffy. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into individual molds or a 1-quart mold.
Chill at least 6 hours or until set.

title: st.  mark's chili recipe
directions: Sear meat, a little at a time.
Chip or grind onions.
Peel and chip garlic.
Mix onions and garlic with meat.
Add tomato paste.
Add seasoning and water.
Stir occasionally.
Cook slowly, about 3 hours.
Parch flour and add to chili just before serving. If too greasy, skim off fat.

title: glorified creamy chicken breasts
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil or oleo.
Place in casserole.
Spoon soup over top.
Sprinkle with pepper and thyme.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: In a medium bowl, combine chicken, 2 tablespoons soy sauce, 2 teaspoons cornstarch and ginger; toss until well blended.
In a small bowl, mix remaining soy sauce, water, sugar and remaining cornstarch.
Set aside.
Heat 2 tablespoons salad oil in skillet. Add chicken and stir over high heat for 3 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Add remaining salad oil to pan and heat.
Add carrots and onion; stir-fry 3 minutes; add zucchini and stir-fry 2 minutes more.
Return chicken to skillet and add soy sauce.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Serve with rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Mix together the sour cream, soups and chicken broth.
Place the chicken breasts in a baking dish. Pour the soup mixture over them. Top with cracker crumbs, and drizzle the crumbs with the melted butter.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until the crackers are well browned.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: bowzer biscuits(your dog will love them!)
directions: Mix first five ingredients in a bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles corn meal.
Beat brown sugar and egg together, then add to flour mixture.
Gradually add 1/2 cup water to make a stiff dough.
Knead on a floured board until dough is smooth and pliable.
Roll out to 1 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters or into squares.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned, about 30 minutes.

title: kings arms sweet potatoes
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash cooked or canned sweet potatoes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except turn mixture into prepared casserole and sprinkle with reserved brown sugar.
Bake at 400° in preheated oven for 30 minutes or may freeze and bake at a later date.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: jalapeno-corn casserole
directions: Cook
rice
according to package directions; set aside. Saute onion,
green pepper and celery in butter until tender. Combine rice,
sauteed
vegetables	and
next
4 ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon
mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pilgrim's 14 bean soup
directions: Catch loon; boil loon.
Loon soup no good, forgot to add salt.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Put oil, zucchini, eggs and dry ingredients (sifted together) into bowl and stir together.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: perfect barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Serve on hot dogs, hamburgers, etc.

title: goodie balls
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut. Refrigerate if using a refrigerated brand of peanut butter, which would be preferable.

title: percy's brunswick stew
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bring to boil and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: pepper steak stir-fry
directions: Mix soy sauce, sugar, garlic powder and ginger in a medium bowl.
Add beef; let stand 10 minutes to marinate.
Drain. Stir-fry beef in hot oil in a large skillet until brown.
Add peppers and onion.
Stir-fry until tender.
Mix broth and cornstarch, add to skillet and bring to a boil for 1 minute. Meanwhile, prepare 4 servings of instant rice.
Add to skillet, mix well and serve.

title: pearl "nanny" fowler's chicken livers with rice
directions: Melt butter in a casserole dish.
Pour in uncooked rice.

Add onion soup and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until rice is tender, but not dry. Ten minutes before rice is ready, roll chicken livers in flour and stick repeatedly with a fork to prevent popping.
Fry until well done and arrange on top of rice. Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Combine margarine or butter, honey and mustard, salt and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake chicken 1 1/4 hours, basting every 15 minutes until chicken is tender and nicely brown.
Good served with rice.

title: cream cheese and olive dip
directions: Whisk all ingredients together.
Make the day before.
Serve with Triscuits, Wheat Thins or chips.

title: roast
directions: Boil Boston Butt or Pic-Nic roast for 1 hour.
Put it into a pan and baste it with sauce.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees. It should fall off of the bone when cut.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Toss all together and chill.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine, pecans and powdered sugar. Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Pare eggplant and cut in slices 1/2-inch thick.
Soak slices in salt water for 1 hour.
Drain and wipe dry.
Dip slices in beaten egg and roll in fine bread or cracker crumbs.
Fry in hot fat (or deep fry) until well browned on both sides.
Serve with catsup or tomato sauce.

title: buttermilk fried cakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar, shortening and soda, mixed with buttermilk.
Sift remaining ingredients and add to mixture. Let mixture stand overnight in refrigerator.
Roll out and cut. Drop in deep, hot fat (375°) and turn over as soon as they rise to the top, nicely browned.
Drain.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.
Glaze, if desired.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thickened.

title: brunswick stew for fifty
directions: Cook and grind all the meats.
Place in a large container (washpot is excellent).
Add all other ingredients except Worcestershire and sugar.
Cook slowly, stirring often, for not less than 2 hours.
Add sugar and Worcestershire the last 30 minutes of cooking time.
Can be cut down for less servings.
When boiling the meats (chicken and beef), be sure to save the broth for the stew.

title: lasagna florentine
directions: In a large pan, cook the first 5 ingredients in olive oil. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool and mix with the cottage cheese, spinach, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and eggs.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine crab meat, sour cream, cream cheese, mayonnaise and seasonings. Place in a casserole. Top with Cheddar cheese and bake in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with party crackers or small rye bread.

title: chicken squares
directions: Blend 2 tablespoons butter and cream cheese until smooth. Add cooked, diced chicken, salt, pepper and milk.

title: cauliflower and peas salad
directions: Wash cauliflower flowerets, drained. Add onion and peas, drained.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in mayonnaise and mix well. Chill before serving. Goes real good with Sunday dinner.

title: grandmother's rice pudding
directions: Heat loganberries and sugar to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cook five minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool. Yields 8 servings.

title: mixed bean pot(gas grill recipe)
directions: Place a large cast-iron skillet on grill.
Add onion, garlic and bacon.
Cook at high flame setting until brown.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Reduce flame setting to low.
Cook about 35 minutes with the grill cover closed or in the 1-inch position, stirring occasionally.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: little smokies
directions: Mix jelly and chili sauce in crock-pot and heat.
Pour Smokies and cook until tender; keep warm.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together; line sides and bottom of greased 9-inch spring-form pan (not all the way up sides).

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in an ovenproof bowl which can be used for serving.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Do not allow mixture to brown on top.
Remove from oven and serve with crackers or chips while warm.
Serves 4 to 6 (appetizer servings).

title: veal chops
directions: Mix bread crumbs with cheese, nutmeg and pepper.
Spread in flat dish.
Put eggs in separate flat dish and beat.
Using bones as handle, dip meat into egg, then press into bread crumbs until coated.
Transfer chops to waxed paper.
With flat side of a cleaver, pound on one side gently to press on crumbs.
Heat 1/4-inch butter in large skillet.
Saute until brown on both sides.
Transfer to paper toweled baking sheet.
Keep warm in 250° oven.

title: nippy nuts
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat; stir in spices.
Add nuts; stir until coated.
Spread in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool on pan.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields 4 cups.

title: microwave beef stroganoff casserole
directions: Combine beef, onion and garlic in 2-quart microproof casserole. Place in oven.
Cook on High 3 minutes.
Pause and stir; cook in microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir in noodles, mushrooms, broth and pepper.
Cover with casserole lid or plastic and cook on half power 11 minutes.
Stir, cover and cook on half power for 11 minutes. Remove from oven and let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Blend in sour cream and sprinkle with parsley before serving.
Serves 6.

title: chicken or turkey hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a large casserole dish or an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: vegetarian stroganoff
directions: Glaze onions and mushrooms sprinkled sparingly with paprika. Add diced burger steak and Parmesan cheese.
Cook under low heat for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring.
Add grape juice; simmer on low for 10 minutes.
Add sour cream, warm gently and serve.

title: twice-baked squash
directions: Halve squash.
Remove seeds; discard.
Place squash, cut side down, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cover; bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes until tender or place in glass dish, put in microwave, cover with wax paper and bake on High for 20 to 30 minutes until squash is tender.
Remove squash pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
In a large mixing bowl, combine squash pulp, spinach, 1/2 cup of the cheese, margarine or butter, bacon, green onion, salt and red pepper.
Fill the squash shells with squash mixture.
Combine remaining cheese and bread crumbs; sprinkle on top of squash.
Place squash in same baking pan.* Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 8 side dish servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well.
Stir in nuts last.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Dip a fork in water and flatten cookies by making a crisscross design.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 250°.

title: thai rice salad with peanut dressing
directions: Bring water to a boil and stir in rice and salt.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Let stand covered 5 minutes.
Transfer to large bowl and cool to room temperature.
Combine peanut butter, vinegar, oil, soy sauce, sugar, ginger, garlic and cayenne.
Peel cucumber and halve lengthwise.
Slice thinly.
Add to rice with chicken, onion and spinach.
Toss.
Add dressing and mix well. Serves 6.

title: low-fat quick cobbler
directions: *Can use juice in place of water.
If fresh fruit, sprinkle with NutraSweet to make juice.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan in oven at 350°.
Mix in small bowl the flour, sugar, egg, juice and vanilla.
Pour evenly over melted margarine; do not stir.
Place peaches over batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip, or serve plain.
Delicious either way.

title: window cleaner
directions: Rub area with an ice cube.
Then scrape with a dull knife. Sponge with dry cleaning solvent.
Allow to air dry.
Wash in hottest water safe for fabric.

title: timothy's white chili
directions: Combine beans, broth, garlic and half the onions in a large soup pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until beans are soft (2 hours or more), adding more broth or water as necessary.

title: layered taco bean dip
directions: In a medium mixing bowl stir together bean dip and taco seasoning mix.
Spread mixture on a 10-inch tray or pie plate. Sprinkle with onions.
Stir together salad dressing and sour cream; then spread over onions.
Top with olives.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Serve with chips.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Blend sugar and margarine in saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Blend hot mixture into beaten eggs slowly.
Add pecans, vanilla and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pasta in pot
directions: Cook shells according to package directions; drain.
Cook ground beef, onions, mushrooms and green pepper; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and sour cream.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer sauce mixture and shells.
Layer with cheese and with cheeses ending up on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is all melted on top.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix soup, water and chilies together to make mixture.
Layer Doritos, 1/2 onion, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 mixture.
Finish with Doritos on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chicken and rice dish
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken, oleo and lemon juice. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Place chicken over rice, covering well. Melt oleo and add lemon juice to it. Brush over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Baste with rest of oleo and lemon juice.

title: pink salad
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to a boil.
Stir.
Stir in jello and let cool.
Stir in 1 cup cottage cheese.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed on the box and stir into mixture.
Add 1 cup of nuts, if desired.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine marshmallows, sugar and flour.
Bring Coke, margarine and cocoa to boil; cool.
Mix dry plus rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: saucy shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish; mix well.
Arrange shrimp in a single layer.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave at High for 6 1/2 to 9 minutes, stirring once, until shrimp are opaque.
Let stand, covered, 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve over rice, if desired.

title: barbecue dip
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat; stir occasionally.

title: minestrone
directions: Saute bacon, onion and ground beef in a large kettle.
Add other ingredients and simmer 1/2 hour. Serve in soup dishes. Good with garlic bread.

title: pasta italiana bake
directions: Brown	meat;
drain.
Add
onion,
green
peppers
and garlic.
Cook
until
tender.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Combine noodles and parsley; toss lightly.
Combine salad dressing, 1/2 cup cheese and eggs; mix well.
Layer noodles, salad dressing mixture and meat sauce in 10 x 6-inch baking
dish.	Top
with
remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sugarless strawberry pie
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together in a saucepan.
Cook until clear, constantly stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin. Refrigerate until partially set, like egg white.
Gently mix in fresh strawberries.
Pour into cooled baked pie shell. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small, bite size pieces.
This should take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover meat.
Cook over kerosene fire (temperature 465°) for about 4 weeks.
This should feed about 3,800 people, but if more people are expected you may add the rabbits.
Do this only if necessary as most people do not like hare in their stew.
Be sure to shop early as elephants are in short supply this year.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles.
Brown beef and onion; add vegetable soup, cheese and tomato sauce to ground beef mixture and heat until cheese is melted.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over drained egg noodles and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to package directions. Beat cream cheese and 10x sugar together.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Put half of the mixture in pie shell. Layer strawberries.
Spread remaining creamed mixture on top. Chill 3 hours.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat well.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Sprinkle with a little nutmeg.
Cook for 40 or 50 minutes at 375° or until thick.

title: cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan melt the margarine or butter; add carrots and celery.
Cook until tender.
Stir in flour and pepper until blended.
Add milk and bratwurst.
Cook and stir over medium heat about 8 minutes or until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 1 minute more.
Add process cheese spread.
Cook, stirring constantly, until process cheese spread is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump 2 cans cherries into pan and dump pineapple into pan. Mix together.
Dump cake mix on the top and spread out.
Dump 2 sticks margarine and layer out on top of cake mix.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage party casserole
directions: Brown the sausage, pour off excess fat.
Saute pepper, onion and celery in excess fat.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown
meat.
Stir
in water and taco mix.
Press rolls into an	ungreased
9 or 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle corn chips on rolls. Add
meat
mixture	and
sour cream.
Top with cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crust is brown.	To serve, surround
with shredded lettuce.
Garnish with avocado and tomato slices.
Serves 6.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until lightly browned, 10 to 12 minutes.
Add beef broth and bouillon.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour into 2 soup bowls (individual).
Place bread on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until brown and bubbly.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Make cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.
Turn upside-down and put on large plate.
Pour Kahlua over cake to absorb thoroughly, but not to excess.
Cut cake in half, horizontally.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar. Chop figs and add part of flour with baking powder.
Add remaining flour.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with egg mixture.
Beat well.
Add honey.
Chop raisins and almonds.
Add to mixture with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pan and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend with other ingredients.
Mixture will be fairly soft.
Chill slightly.
Form into a ball and chill until party time.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans on wax paper.
Roll ball in this to cover.

title: homemade chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Make sugar there are no lumps. Add other ingredients.
Boil slow for 5 minutes.
Ice layers while icing is still hot.

title: herb seasoned beef tenderloin
directions: Combine mustard and olive oil; brush on all sides of tenderloin.
Combine pepper, oregano, thyme, chives, garlic and salt.
Pat seasoning mixture on all sides of roast.
Place tenderloin on a rack in a large shallow pan.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Insert meat thermometer.
Roast at 425° for about 45 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 140° for rare.
Remove from oven and let stand 45 minutes, then wrap and chill.
Before serving meat allow tenderloin to stand at room temperature for 2 hours.
Slice and serve at room temperature. Serves 12.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Add salt to cabbage; let set 1 hour.
Squeeze out.
Combine remaining ingredients; boil for 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour over vegetables.
Stir and refrigerate.
(May also be frozen.)

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Dice vegetables, add mayonnaise or yogurt, salt and pepper; mix well.

title: much more than mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine for 5 minutes.
Add green onions, pepper, celery, salt, pepper, parsley and m.s.g.
Cook 3 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Add mayonnaise; stir in.
Set aside.

title: "stina" dill pickles
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil.
To each quart jar, use 2
heads
of
dill and 2 cloves of garlic.
Fill jars with small cucumbers.
Add vinegar water; seal.

title: southwest casserole
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Mix together dry ingredients (I use 1/4 cup baking mix in place of flour, baking powder and salt) and beat into eggs with a wire whisk.
Add the cottage cheese and mix well.
Add the other cheeses, margarine and chiles; mix well.

title: better brussels sprouts
directions: Cut off stems from sprouts and remove outer yellow layer.
Cut small x in bottom of each.
Rinse in cold water; drain and pat dry.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Beat eggs; add milk. Sift dry ingredients into batter. Beat until smooth. Add melted butter last. Let set one hour. Mix again before cooking in butter or margarine. Use hot pan.

title: wendy's chili
directions: Mix all together and heat up.

title: white christmas salad
directions: Bring
pineapple,
lemon
juice
and
sugar
to
boil. Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup
cold
water and add to hot juice. Stir well and cool	until
mixture begins to gel.
Add cheese, nuts, celery and
cherries.
Carefully fold in whipped topping and turn into oiled mold.
Chill until firm.

title: pumpkin mousse pie
directions: Prepare pie filling as directed on pkg. with 3/4 cup milk. Blend in pumpkin, spice and 2 cups whipped topping. Spoon into pie shell. Chill at least 4 hours. Spread remaining whipped topping on top.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine sugar, flour and spices; mix with apples.

title: easy boston baked beans
directions: After browning the bacon, saute onion in the bacon grease. Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: crunchy baked chicken and potatoes(low-fat)
directions: Scrub potatoes; piece with fork.
Place in microwave-safe baking dish.
Microwave on High 8 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops well on both sides in skillet.
Place chops in 2-quart casserole.

title: pol's apple cake
directions: Blend eggs, oil
and
sugar
until creamy.
Add flour a little at a
time.
Beat
well.
Batter
will be stiff.
Peel, core and chop apples.
Fold in apples, coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven
for 1
hour.
Remove
from
oven.
Cool
in pan 30 minutes.
Mix butter, brown sugar and milk in saucepan.
Boil three minutes and pour over warm cake.

title: tender swiss steak
directions: Brown meat with cooking oil.
Add sliced onion, soup, tomatoes and half a can of water.
Cook in a 325° oven for 1 to 2 hours or in crock-pot for 5 to 6 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake in two 9-inch layers in greased and floured pans.
After cake is cool, take a thread and wrap around the layers and pull. This will cut the cake into 4 thin layers.
Put 1 layer on bottom of punch bowl. Spread cooled vanilla pudding on that layer, then spread Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Put pie filling on top of Cool Whip. Keep on doing the same with the other cake pieces. End with the pie filling on top.
Dip with a spoon.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk in pan.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Fold in oats and peanuts.
Drop by scant tablespoonfuls on wax paper.
Only makes about 27 cookies, so triple the recipe to make 7 dozen.
If you do triple the recipe, add extra oats, at least 1 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate chess squares
directions: Combine flour and powdered sugar; cut in 1/2 cup margarine with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press mixture evenly into bottom of a 9-inch square pan lined with heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add 2 tablespoons margarine and eggs; beat 2 1/2 minutes at medium speed with an electric mixer.
Add milk and vanilla, mixing well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture over crust; bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Cut into squares while warm.
Let cool completely before removing from pan.

title: salmon party ball
directions: Drain salmon and flake with fork.
Add cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish and liquid smoke. Mix well.
Chill overnight.
Roll into log.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Mix beans, soup, milk and 3/4 can onion rings together.
Add pepper to taste.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Crush remaining onion rings.
Garnish top. Bake for another 5 minutes.

title: chicken chutney stir fry
directions: Mix cornstarch, soy sauce and chutney. Heat oil in 10 inch skillet or wok over medium high heat. Add chicken and vegetables; stir fry 5 to 7 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink in center. Stir in chutney mixture. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened. Serve over rice. Sprinkle with peanuts.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Heat up refried beans.
Put in cheese until melted, then add the salsa.
Mix up really good.
Serve warm with chips.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Take 2 cans of soup, put in dish and add one can of water and stir together.
Then put most of sour cream in with and stir. Then stir in hamburger, then put potatoes on top.
Then melted butter on that.
Then Ritz cracker on top.
Put in oven and bake at 350° for 45 minutes until brown on top.

title: old fashion multi-layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a very large mixing bowl, empty cake mix packets and run mixer through dry mix until most of the lumps are gone.
Then mix in eggs, water and softened butter.
Dip 1 cup batter into 9-inch cake pans; spread around pan with back of spoon until evenly distributed.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn out from pan as soon as you remove from oven.
Yield:
Approximately 11 layers.

title: hungarian chicken and rice
directions: Saute onion in oil in large Dutch oven type pan.
Add chicken, giblets (hearts and stomachs), carrots (cleaned and cut in 2-inch pieces) and salt and pepper and sprinkle with paprika until covered (coated).
Cook covered over low heat until chicken is done.
Remove chicken (leave in carrots and giblets) and add parsley, celery leaves, water and rice.
Recover and cook over low heat until rice is cooked.
Stir often to prevent sticking and burning.

title: italian pork chops
directions: Trim pork chops.
Brown in oil on both sides; drain.
Pour 1 full jar Ragu Italian cooking sauce over chops.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: butternut cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix as directed.
(Add 1 teaspoon butternut flavoring to batter.)

title: date nut krispies
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and beat well.
Melt butter in saucepan, pour in egg mixture and dates.
Stir and cook until mixture thickens and turns dark brown (3 to 5 minutes after mixture boils).
Add vanilla.
Remove from heat, add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Cool slightly.
Make into small balls or into long rolls like refrigerator cookies.
Roll in coconut, nuts or powdered sugar.
Put in refrigerator to harden.
These keep indefinitely in the long rolls and can be sliced as needed.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add salt to taste.
Mix soup, sour cream, cheese and butter.
Spread over thawed potatoes. Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Bake 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Add rice, onion soup and beef broth.
Stir; bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: everylasting play dough
directions: Combine the flour, salt and cream of tartar in a medium saucepan.
Add water, oil and food coloring.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture is very thick and sticks together. (This will take just a few minutes.)
Remove play dough from pan and knead until smooth.
It is now ready to play with or store in an airtight container.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in skin until a fork pierces easily.
Drain water and cool potatoes; remove skin.
Dice potatoes.
Cook bacon and drain.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over potatoes; mix well.

title: punch for 100
directions: Mix sugar and jello.
Warm part of water to dissolve jello and sugar.
Cool and add rest of ingredients.
Can be frozen and add ginger ale before serving.

title: baked apple butter
directions: Combine applesauce, sugar, vinegar, cloves and cinnamon in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 2 1/2 hours or until mixture is thick and almost transparent; stir occasionally during baking.
Pour into jars and store in refrigerator.

title: jovita's marinated pea & bean saladwarren, texas
directions: Drain cans of peas and beans.

title: christmas fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in Part 1 and chill.
Add Part 2 ingredients before serving.

title: pear relish
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Seal in hot jars; store in dark place.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine and let cool the dates, soda and boiling water.
Mix together brown sugar, egg and melted butter and add to date mixture.
Add to this, flour, nut meats and vanilla.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes two loaves.
Pan size, 4 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger; add oregano and garlic powder.
Add tomato sauce and cool, then add the cheese.
Put in buns and wrap in foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans with salt (drain if using canned beans and omit salt).
Combine milk, soup and pepper.
Pour over beans in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add 1/2 can onions.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Garnish with 1/2 can onions and pimiento.
Bake 5 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple strudel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put a thick layer of apples into a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture. Dot with lumps of butter.
Into a mixing bowl, sift 1 cup sugar, the baking powder, flour and the salt.
Mix in the egg until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mailanderli(swiss sugar cookies)
directions: Beat butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, beating until very pale, about 5 minutes.
Add yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla.
Sift flour into butter mixture and fold in thoroughly.

title: dirty rice
directions: Make roux by heating the oil, then add flour and stir
until dark.
Add onions, celery and garlic.
Cook until withered. Add finely chopped or ground giblets or round steak.
If using steak, stir until red disappears. Add all other ingredients and chicken broth.
Cook over very low heat, covered, until the mixture is consistent in thick gravy. Add cooked rice, salt and pepper to taste.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown meat, chopped onion and pepper in pan.
Salt and pepper. Sprinkle chili powder over all.
Add 4 cans of beans and stir.
Add brown sugar and ketchup.
Stir, cover and bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove from bone.
Tear tortillas in pieces and line bottom of a baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, except cheese, and add in layers of tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese, saving layer of cheese for top.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter; add and brown flour, salt, pepper and sugar. Remove from heat and add slowly French onion dip or sour cream and onion.
Grate Swiss cheese and layer with the first mixture and the green beans.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes in 2-quart casserole, uncovered.
Can use 3 packages frozen green beans, cooked and drained.

title: my husband's favorite("fast and easy")
directions: Brown the ground meat mix.
Drain grease.
Add 2 tablespoons of Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Simmer for about 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup syrup and can of baked beans. Simmer again for 45 minutes.

title: grandma potoczny's meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except olive oil and garlic.
Wet hands, then roll meat balls; wet hands occasionally.
In pan, brown 2 cloves of garlic in oil.
Take out garlic when browned, then brown meatballs (no lid).

title: steamed persimmon pudding
directions: Add all ingredients to the persimmon pulp in order given.
May add nut meats and/or raisins.
Pour into greased mold and cover tightly.
Set in pan of water and steam 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot or cold with your choice of sauce, ice cream or whipped cream. May add chopped dates, too.

title: farmers' seafood boil
directions: In a large boiling pot, bring a gallon of water, crab boil and salt to a boil.
Add potatoes and boil for 10 minutes.
Add onions and sausage and boil for 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and corn.
Boil for 5 minutes more.
Drain and serve with crusty bread and a cold beverage.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add the beaten eggs, then the bananas.
Mix baking soda, salt and flour, then combine with other mixture.
Then add nuts and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: monster cookies(can double.)
directions: Mix together all ingredients in order given.
Drop on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: acini de pepe salad
directions: Cook noodles as box directs.
Drain fruit and save juices.

title: herb chicken
directions: This fits in a square or small oblong Pyrex dish.
Grease dish and sprinkle rice in bottom.
Place chicken pieces over rice. Sprinkle dry onion soup over chicken and add undiluted soup.
Pour milk over this.
Sprinkle with paprika; seal with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 325° then bake uncovered for 3/4 to 1 hour or until chicken is browned.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Combine peanut butter, milk and cream cheese in large mixing bowl on low speed.
Add powdered sugar and whipped topping, mix until smooth.
Pour into a Bama 9-inch graham cracker crust. Freeze until firm.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: yellow whipped cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 2 round layer pans.

title: date nut bread
directions: Place dates and nutmeats on platter and sprinkle with baking soda.
Then pour boiling water over and let stand until cool.

title: salsa cruda
directions: Chop each ingredient by hand.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Taste and adjust the seasonings.
Let the salsa stand for at least 30 minutes.
Stir well before serving.
Makes 2 cups.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and serve with fruit.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add soda to sour cream and add to ingredients with flour.
Fold in stiff egg whites.
Pour into tubed pan (greased and floured) and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Place on damp cloth for 10 minutes.

title: pear preserves
directions: Peel, core and quarter enough to make 1 quart of pears. Combine and boil for 5 minutes, 1 cup water and sugar.
Add pears to syrup and bring gently to a boil.
Then boil rapidly until pears are clear and tender.
Syrup should be thick.
Pack in hot, sterilized jars and seal immediately.
Lemon or pineapple slices may be added for flavor.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Beat egg and add sugar and oil.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla; mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Layer lettuce, mayo, bacon, peas, onion, green bell pepper and cheese.
Start over and finish repeating layers until all ingredients are used up.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: In a separate pot over medium heat, bring broth to a boil. In separate large bowl, combine the beef, pork, 3 eggs, bread crumbs, basil, parsley and 1/2 cup Parmesan.
Mix well and form into bite size balls.
Drop the balls into the broth.
Add escarole into broth.
When balls rise to the top, they are cooked, about 5 to 7 minutes.
When escarole is wilted, it is done.
In a separate bowl, combine the remaining 5 eggs with the remaining cheese.
Pour this mixture into soup, stirring continuously until the egg is cooked.

title: fresh apple and orange bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together into a bowl. In a blender, place shortening, orange juice, eggs and sugar; blend well.
Add apples and the orange.
Blend only until the fruit is chopped.
Add the raisins and nut meats and stir into the flour mixture.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add everything except shrimp.
Blend well, then add shrimp.
Let set overnight to blend flavor.

title: orange marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients in jar.
Shake.
Brush onto beef, pork or poultry and grill.

title: dr.  bird cake
directions: Blend all together and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Use a Bundt pan or angel food pan.
If you use a mixer, fold in the bananas and nuts by hand.

title: grilled applesauce cake
directions: Combine sugar, brown sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Stir in applesauce.
Sift together flour, pumpkin pie spice, soda and salt; add to mixture, mixing well.
Pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Preheat gas grill.
Cook with cover down using indirect cooking method on high setting 40 minutes, or until done.
