Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly on wire rack.
Combine confectioners sugar and apple juice; drizzle over cake.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in water.
Add frozen juices and stir in ginger ale just before serving.

title: carrot spice cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Thinly slice potatoes enough to fill 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add onions and ham.
In bowl, combine butter, soup, milk, flour, garlic powder, salt, pepper and cheese.
Heat for about 4 minutes in microwave.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 400° at least 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple roll
directions: Bring to a
boil
1 1/2 cups sugar and water; set aside to cool.
Mix
together
remaining
ingredients.
Mix together and roll
to
1/4-inch
thickness.
Slice
apples over pastry. Sprinle with a little sugar, cinnamon and dot of butter.
Roll like jelly roll and cut in
slices.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour liquid over this and bake at 350° until apples are done.

title: nasturtium salad
directions: Peel and thinly slice cucumbers.
Wash nasturtium leaves and drain.
Mix wine, vinegar, oil, pepper and tarragon in blender. When ready to serve, combine cucumbers, nasturtium leaves and dressing and toss gently.
Garnish with nasturtium flowers with leaves.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Dissolve sugar in water before allowing to boil.
Cook to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo and nuts.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Makes 6 or 7 small.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine juice from pineapple, sugar, cranberries, raisins, spices and salt.
Cook to boiling; lower heat and simmer for 25 minutes.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: no bake peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir over high heat for 5 minutes or until butter is melted. Remove from heat; add peanut butter and oats.
Drop on wax paper.

title: skewered salad
directions: For Each Salad:
Arrange zucchini, tomatoes and mushrooms on skewer.
Insert skewer in lettuce wedge.
Serve with dressing.

title: chunky chicken hash casserole
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Add chicken, beans or peas, pimentos and pepper.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly hot.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook in skillet about 10 to 12 minutes.
When done, stir in 1 teaspoon soda quickly.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet and spread quickly.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the first three ingredients.
Then add flour, sugar, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in buttermilk until all is well mixed.
Pour into a large sheet pan.
Make sure it's the one with sides.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: *pecan date pudding
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut up dates in a mixing bowl.
Sprinkle soda over them and add boiling water.
Stir a few times and let stand.
Cream shortening and sugar; beat in egg.
Mix in flour, then date mixture and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 9 (3-inch) squares. Freezes well.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer each item, ending with Miracle Whip to seal in vegetables.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: holiday ribbon mold
directions: Dissolve red gelatin with 1 cup boiling water; stir in 3/4 cup cold water.
Pour into 5 cup mold.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until set, but not firm.
Dissolve lime gelatin with 1 cup boiling water; stir in 3/4 cup cold water.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or until cooled.
Pour over red gelatin, gently place marshmallows in gelatin.
Refrigerate four hours until firm.
Unmold.

title: special bars
directions: Put Rice Krispies in a mixing bowl and set aside.
Boil sugar, Karo and butter together for 1 minute. Take off stove and add the peanut butter. Pour over the Rice Krispies and stir.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and press down.
Melt together in a double boiler the chips, stirring occasionally, being careful not to splash with water.
Spread melted chips over the Rice Krispies in the pan.
Cool completely, but cut before it hardens.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add corn, tomato sauce, salsa and taco seasoning mix.
Simmer, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes.
In a separate bowl, combine cottage cheese, eggs and oregano.

title: lazy day casserole
directions: Brown onion and hamburger over medium heat in skillet.
Add all other ingredients except peas and cheese.
Cook 10 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Stir in peas.
Store overnight in plastic container in refrigerator.
The next day, place in lightly buttered casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes and serve.

title: stir-fry
directions: Cook rice, scramble eggs and set aside. Put oleo in skillet. Brown chicken. Add rice and soy sauce.
Add eggs and veggies. Stir until cooked.
Serve while hot.

title: ever ready muffins
directions: Mix cereal with sugar, flour, salt and soda in large bowl. Add eggs, oil and milk. Mix well.
Store in refrigerator in sealed container.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes in greased muffin pan.
Do not stir after refrigerating.
Batter will keep up to 6 weeks.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Mix fruits, nuts and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add to fruit mixture.
Bake at 250° for little over an hour.

title: mom's baked pork chops
directions: Layer the pork chops in an oven pan.
Mix garlic, onion and basil into mushroom soup.
Pour mushroom mixture over pork chops and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Add the potatoes, use a spoon and put some of the mushroom gravy over the potatoes.
Bake for 45 minutes more.

title: copper carrots
directions: Scrape and slice carrots.
Boil in salted water until tender. Then cool and drain.
Alternate layers of carrots, then green pepper rings and onion rings.
Make a marinade of remaining ingredients; beat well until blended.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: brownies
directions: Melt together cocoa and margarine; add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when done baking.

title: party mix
directions: In medium saucepan, melt chocolate morsels, peanut butter and margarine.
Pour over cereal and peanuts which have been placed in a large bowl.
Stir gently.
Cool completely.
Powder with confectioners sugar to coat.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to soft ball stage (234° to 240°). Add raw peanuts.
Continue cooking until light brown in color and gives hard crack test (300° to 310°).
Remove from fire and add butter, vanilla and soda.
Mix well.
Pour on a buttered cookie sheet and spread thin as possible.
When nearly cool, turn over and stretch to desired thinness.
Break into pieces.

title: toast
directions: Insert bread in toaster and toast to desired doneness, then butter and put on your favorite jam.

title: party chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Place slices of cheese over chicken.
Mix together soup and wine and pour over chicken and cheese.
Mix margarine with stuffing mix and sprinkle over top of chicken. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut bell peppers in half.
Discard seeds and membranes.
In large pot of boiling water, blanch peppers for 3 minutes.
Invert to drain.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in mixer; add eggs, one at a time, beating each lightly.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with lemon extract.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: dirt
directions: Crush cookies with rolling pin in a zipper-style plastic bag or in food processor.
Pour milk in a large bowl and add pudding mix.
Beat for 2 minutes, then stand for 2 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and half of crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon crushed cookies in each of 8 to 10 (7-ounce) paper cups.
Add pudding and then top with remaining crushed cookies.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Decorate with gummy worms.

title: date bars
directions: Sprinkle soda over dates.
Add boiling water and butter.
Cool. Add rest of the ingredients and blend.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 10 x 12-inch pan.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350° or until it tests done with toothpick.
Cool.
Cut in bars. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: chrust(polish)
directions: Add salt to eggs and beat 10 minutes.
Add sugar and flavoring; beat until well blended.
Fold in flour.
Transfer to a well-floured board and knead until dough blisters.
Cut in halves. Roll very thin and cut into 4-inch strips (long).
Slit each piece in center and pull one end through the slit.
Fry in hot fat until lightly browned.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Soak eggplant overnight or all day in salt water.
Steam eggplant until almost done (about 20 minutes). Drain. Soak breads in milk.
Saute vegetables in butter about 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. This can be made with zucchini squash.

title: stir-fry american style
directions: In small bowl, combine beef or chicken with soy sauce, sherry and ginger.
Let stand 15 to 30 minutes.
Preheat 1 tablespoon oil in wok, uncovered, at medium-high, about 2 minutes.
Add carrots; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add reserved mushroom liquid; cover and steam 4 minutes.
Remove carrots.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Slice apples.
Put cream cheese into a bowl and pour 1/2 of the caramel dip over the cream cheese.
Heat in microwave about 3 minutes on High.
Stir until mixed and creamy.
Dip apple slices.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Place 1/2 of bread cubes in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish. Mix together onion, celery, peppers, mayonnaise and fish.
Spread over bread cubes.
Add a little salt and pepper to taste.
Add remaining bread cubes over top.

title: margaret's raw apple cake
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together.
In a separate bowl mix: flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix all together and add to apple mixture with walnuts.
Stir with spoon by hand.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes, depending on pan size.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine milk and cold water; heat.
Pour hot liquid over butter, sugar and salt; stir until butter melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups flour, dissolved yeast and oats.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, soda and salt.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and sour cream alternately.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in tube pan.

title: donna coursen's zucchini rounds
directions: Stir together Bisquick, cheese and pepper.
Stir in beaten eggs until mixture is moistened.
Fold in zucchini.
In large skillet, melt butter and oil over medium heat.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of mixture for each round.
Cook four rounds at a time, 2 to 3 minutes on each side, until light brown.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: norwegian coleslaw
directions: Chop cabbage, bell pepper, onion and celery.
Mix well and let set 1 hour.
Combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed. Bring to a boil; cook 3 minutes.
Let cool; pour over slaw and chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with cherries.

title: cheese torte
directions: Mix egg yolks, milk and sugar in saucepan.
Cook until custard like consistency.
Add gelatine mixed with water.
Cool.
While the mixture cools, make a graham cracker crust by crushing the graham crackers until they are fine.
Mix with 1/2 cup melted butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Press the crumb mixture into a greased, lined torte pan.
Save 1 cup of crumbs for top.
Whip egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Whip cream until stiff.
Beat the cooled custard mixture, cheese and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites and whipped cream. Pour mixture into pan lined with crumbs.
Sprinkle the top with reserved crumb mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with cherry or blueberry pie filling if desired.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: white butter cream frosting
directions: Add vanilla to margarine.
Slowly add sugar, beating constantly.
Add milk as necessary.
(Suggested frosting for Mayonnaise Cake.)

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Grease pan.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Stir spaghetti sauce into meat.
Combine spaghetti, eggs and parmesan. Place spaghetti mixture into pan.
Pour meat mixture on spaghetti. Cover with mozzarella.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into slices and serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and milk.
Mix together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Spread batter on bottom of casserole dish.
Spoon fruit on top of batter. Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over fruit, then pour juice over.
Bake in slow oven until done.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat in separate bowl the buttermilk, butter and eggs.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Beat them until blended only.
Grease pan.
Bake at 425°.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Blend together in mixer.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Especially good with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: frozen banana cream
directions: Combine banana, lime juice and sugar and mix thoroughly. Using an electric mixer, whip the cream with the salt until it is very stiff.
Fold bananas into the cream and spread into a large shallow baking dish.
Freeze solid.

title: meat pies
directions: Brown meat.
Add chopped onion and mushrooms.
Cook until onions turn transparent.
Set aside.
Cut bread dough into 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Roll pieces out to form 6 to 8-inch ovals.
Put meat mix and grated cheese in each oval and fold in half.
Seal round side with a fork and brush with egg.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.
Cut in half and top with sauce and cheese.
Serve hot.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix vanilla and brown sugar; add the sour cream.
Put vanilla, brown sugar and sour cream in a small bowl.
Put fruit in another bowl and serve.

title: smoked salmon chowder
directions: Cook bacon until browned. Drain all but 1 tablespoon bacon fat and saute onion and celery. Add flour and seasonings until bubbly. Add chicken broth and remaining ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes before serving.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in bran.
Combine egg, banana, milk and salad oil.
Add liquid ingredients all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just till flour mixture is moistened.
Fill well-greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake muffins in hot oven 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or till done. Makes about 12 muffins.

title: mom's custard pie
directions: Line unpricked pie shell with a double thickness of heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes.
Remove from the oven and set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat the eggs just until combined.
Blend in sugar, salt and vanilla.
Stir in milk. Carefully pour into crust.
Cover edges of pie with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Store in the refrigerator. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: bud's birthday cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Add buttermilk.
Mix in spices and vanilla.
Stir in prunes and nuts. Grease and lightly flour a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour in cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Layer dish with 8 slices of bread.
Cover with slices of ham and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt and pour over bread.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
When ready to cook, add melted butter to crushed corn flakes and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Good morning!

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and 1 tablespoon milk in large bowl until smooth.
Gently stir in 1/2 of whipped topping.
Spread in bottom of crust.
Pour 2 cups milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with shaved Hershey chocolate candy bar.
Refrigerate 4 hours before serving.

title: corn bread
directions: Cook in saucepan the water, corn meal and salt until thick, stirring constantly.
Add eggs, sugar, flour, milk and baking powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: linda's homemade chili sauce
directions: In small skillet, saute bell pepper and onion,1 to 2 minutes. Add garlic, ketchup and Chili powder. Mix well. Heat thoroughly. Makes about 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: tea biscuits
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture is like coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once.
Stir with fork to ball stage. Knead lightly, about 10 times. Roll or pat dough 1/2 to 1-inch thick. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°. Makes 16 medium biscuits.

title: apple brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in apples and nuts. Spread in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit bars
directions: Grease and flour large pan.
Cover bottom of pan with chopped nuts (pecans).
Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour.
Fold in chopped pineapple, cherries and coconut.
Mix all up and spread over nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
When cool, cut in bars.

title: angel food cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in coconut and vanilla.
Roll dough into small balls.
Dip top of cookie into water, then into white sugar. Bake on greased cookie sheet 12 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven. Makes 4 dozen.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all these well.
Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: winter land pudding
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and add raisins.
Put batter in greased and floured pan (deep loaf type).
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over batter.
Bake until the cake is done. Has its own sauce.
Use whipped cream when served.

title: shrimp soup dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender with lid and process until smooth.
Use a rubber spatula to scrape sides down, if necessary. Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Combine and drop on waxed paper to set.

title: lynda's coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add flavors. Add eggs, one at a time. Mix well, using high speed with electric mixer. Sift flour and salt together, then add slowly. Fold in coconut. Bake in a well-greased and floured 10-inch stem pan or a "Bundt" pan for about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Bake at 325°.

title: batter pie
directions: You will need a 2-quart saucepan.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine juices, water and Kool-Aid.
Mix well.
When ready to serve, add 7-Up or ginger ale.
Scoop sherbet on top.
Kool-Aid flavors and sherbet flavors can vary.
Float fruit on top.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Combine ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into pie plate.
Drain 1 (15 ounce) can peaches (fresh is good too), saving 3 tablespoons juice.
Pour peaches over mixture.
Mix and beat 2 to 3 minutes 1 ounce package cream cheese, 3 tablespoons peach juice and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spoon cheese mixture to 1 inch of edge of pie plate.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: ninfa's green sauce(guacamole dip)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in the blender, and blend until of sauce consistency.

title: boterkoek(dutch butter cookies)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix to form a supple dough.
Place in greased spring-form pan, 10 or 11-inch.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°. Edges should be light brown.
Remove from pan and top with fresh fruit, i.e., kiwi and strawberries.
Slice and serve.

title: cherry sauce
directions: Stir in 1/4 cup finely chopped walnuts.
Serve hot or cold.

title: self filled cupcakes
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sugar, egg, salt and chocolate chips.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Drop 1 teaspoon cream cheese mixture into each cupcake. Bake as directed on package.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with the milk until thick.
Mix in sour cream and fold in whipped topping.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas, then cover with 1/2 pudding mix.
Repeat 2 layers.
Sprinkle crushed wafers on top.
Refrigerate.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Cover with Chinese noodles and bake 15 minutes more.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter; add flour and blend.
Add milk and blend.
Remove from heat.
Add egg yolks, crabmeat, salt, pepper and cheese.
Put in casserole with cheese on top and bake until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tasty baked beans
directions: Open large can of beans.
Add sugar, catsup, molasses and Karo.
Mix well.
Place all ingredients in a large baking dish. Cut the onion into 1/4-inch pieces and add to the bean mixture along the top, bottom and sides of dish.
Place strips of bacon across top of beans.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until bacon is done.

title: sand pudding
directions: Mix instant vanilla pudding as directed on package and let stand 5 minutes.
Pour in Cool Whip and mix together.
Layer crushed cookies, then whipped topping and keep adding in layers.

title: mary belle's yeast rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients (Crisco mixture) and let cool. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 water (cup).
Beat eggs and add to cool Crisco mixture.
Blend Crisco mixture and yeast mixture into flour until it makes a stiff dough.
Let mixture stand and rise until double in size.
Punch down.
Fold in shape of rolls; roll in butter and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 425° until brown. (Melt in your mouth.)

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook onion, oil and sugar in a large pan until light brown. Add ground beef; crumble up and brown, stirring frequently.
Drain off grease.
Add tomatoes, cooked spaghetti and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover with lid and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir often.
Pour out in dish and put cheese on top, if desired.

title: judy's fruit dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together until fluffy.
Chill slightly. Serve with fresh fruit pieces.
Pretend there are no calories in the dip.
Enjoy!

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: chicken dinner pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry as directed, except roll 2/3 of pastry for bottom crust; fit into 9-inch pie pan.
Roll remainder into rectangle about 10 x 6-inch.
Cut rectangle into 12 strips, each 1/2-inch wide.
Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in chicken broth and cream.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Make lattice top using pastry strips.
Trim:
turn edges of bottom crust over strips.
Seal and flute.
Cover edge with 2 to 3 inches of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning.
Remove foil last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bean pot
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rosamarina salad
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice.
To pineapple juice, add egg, flour and sugar.
Stir and cook until thick.
Let cool.
Cook Rosamarina; rinse well.
Mix. Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Next day, add fruit (drained) and fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate covered until ready to use.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa into bowl.
Stir in milk and melted butter. Blend in nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Combine brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa and sprinkle over the top.
Pour hot water over entire batter.
Bake 45 minutes.
During baking, cake mixture rises to top and chocolate sauce settles to bottom.
Serve warm spooned into sauce dishes with whipped cream.
Makes 9 servings.

title: corn with onions
directions: Layer sliced onions and corn in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole. Cover with foil and bake at 400°
for 1 hour.
Saute 1/2 to 1 cup chopped onion.
Make a white sauce with butter, flour and milk. Add sauteed onion, pimento, salt, pepper and cheese until melted. Pour over corn.
Bake in oven about 10 minutes until bubbly.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cook until tender and drain.
Beat softened cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Also real onion if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Mash the cheeses with a fork.
Mix in onion, pecans and parsley.
Chill for 2 hours. Form into a ball or make small 1 inch balls.
Roll balls in a mixture of chopped pecans and parsley.
Put toothpicks in small balls.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Heat juice, sugar, vinegar and spices to boiling.
Add peaches and heat 15 minutes.
Store in covered container.

title: chili
directions: Cook beef, sausage, onion and garlic in skillet until meat is brown.
Drain.
Put meat mixture into crock-pot and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours, stirring frequently or until meat and beans are tender.
Serve.
Top with shredded cheese and side of cornbread.
Found in bread section.
Serves 8.

title: apple smiles
directions: Spread one side of each apple slice with peanut butter.
Place three or four tiny marshmallows on top of the peanut butter on one slice.
Then top with another apple slice.
Squeeze gently.
Eat right away.
Makes 6 to 8.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Mix flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Stir together the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Combine sugar and next 3 ingredients in a small saucepan over medium-high heat; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Stir into sauerkraut mixture. Cover and chill for 8 hours or overnight.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bananas, and stir.
Before serving, add sliced bananas.
You may substitute cherry pie filling or add some fresh peaches, etc. to change it up.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Cream 1/2 cup sour
cream
and one 3 ounce cream cheese thoroughly for dressing.
Mix all ingredients.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Combine chicken, sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Turn into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine cracker crumbs and margarine; spread over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: creamy italian dressing
directions: In a small bowl, mix all ingredients until smooth.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: eggplant supreme
directions: Cut up peeled eggplant and steam in a little water on low heat until tender.
Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add cooked eggplant.
Add Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce; stir. Add cheese and olives.
Taste before adding any salt for the cheese is salty.
Put in baking dish and cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Serves 6.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Mix butter and cheese well.
Blend in flour, pepper and cereal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for approximately 12 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cut sweet potatoes in chunks.
Leave skins on.
Cook until soft.
Mash after removing skins, then mix with other ingredients and put in baking dish.
Spread with topping.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Blend potatoes with powdered sugar.
Mix in coconut and salt. Shape
into
tiny
balls and dip into semi-sweet chocolate.
Chill on waxed paper.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in crust.
Chill for 1 hour.
Makes 2.

title: barbecued potatoes in foil
directions: Fold two 24-inch long sheets of heavy-duty foil in half. Place 1 sheet crosswise over the other.
Coat generously with oil. Combine potatoes and onion in center of foil.
Mix in butter and season with salt and pepper.
Close foil tightly, forming large bag.
Serves 4.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix soup mix and sour cream with spinach.
Top with buttered crumbs and bake at 300° until mixture bubbles.

title: captain crunch candy
directions: In a large bowl mix the first three ingredients together. Melt almond bark & pour over cereal mix.
Stir well to coat & spread out on 3 lightly greased cookie sheets.
Cool completely. Break into pieces and store in zip lock bags.
Freezes well.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: western bean casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet in butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Garlic powder and spoonful of brown sugar may be added, if desired.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Garnish with bacon strips.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Crisp bacon under broiler.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: In 2-quart casserole, melt 2 tablespoons oleo.
Add enough walnuts and pecans (chopped) to cover bottom of casserole.
Cut refrigerator biscuits in quarters.
Place on top of nuts.
Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon together.
Shake mixture over biscuits.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Crust and Topping:
Mix together until crumbly.
Press 2/3 of the mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple juice
directions: Let set for 24 hours.
Strain through a cheese cloth, mix juice with sugar (for 10 cups, 1/2 cup of sugar.)
And add 1/2 to 1 can of frozen apple juice concentrate as for your own taste.
Place in glass jars with seals.

title: baked onions
directions: Peel and cook the onions on medium heat until nearly done. Mix the honey, butter and ketchup or chili sauce and add.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: quick quiche
directions: Mix mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk until blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Can be used for an appetizer, brunch or a light lunch.

title: hawaiian chicken with kumquats
directions: Place chicken in casserole.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake 375° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: ginger puffs
directions: Put soda in hot water and other ingredients.
Add the soda to the hot water and the other ingredients and enough flour to be firm.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: double chocolate fantasy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine butter and cookie crumbs.
Press in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour condensed milk evenly over the crumbs.
Combine the M&M's, coconut and nuts. Sprinkle evenly over milk and crumbs.
Press in lightly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: waffle batter
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar and salt.
Beat in remaining ingredients with rotary beater. Cover; let rise in warm place (85°), about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir down; cover and refrigerate overnight or until ready to use.
Bake in waffle iron.

title: apple and peach dumplings
directions: Separate biscuits into 2 sections.
Enclose quartered fruit in biscuit half and seal edges.
Put into baking dish.
Mix butter, sugar, and water.
Pour mixture over the fruit filled biscuit halves.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: orange delight
directions: Put cottage cheese through blender until it is the consistency of sour cream.
Sprinkle jello over cottage cheese; mix well.
Add fruit, then fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.
Contains 1/2 protein, 1/2 fruit and 20 optional calories.

title: pigs wrapped in blankets
directions: Wash the rice; mix with the meat, onions and seasoning. Simmer about 10 minutes; cool.
Separate the cabbage leaves and boil in salt water for 10 minutes.
Drain.

title: pickled beets
directions: Make solution of equal parts of water, sugar and vinegar. Bring to a boil.
Using small beets makes a better pickle.
Wash and trim stems to about 1 1/2 to 2 inches.
Cook in a large pot until tender.
Cool and slip off skins and tops.
Rinse just slightly and pack into hot jars.
Pour hot vinegar solution to within 1/2 inch of top of jar.
Put into boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
The jars should seal.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Empty can of cherry pie filling into 8-inch pie pan.
Cover with cake mix.
Drizzle melted margarine over cake mix.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: creamed fresh peas with new potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and boil until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain and remove loose skins. Toss hot peeled potatoes in 2 to 3 tablespoons butter until each potato is lightly coated.
Place in a serving bowl and keep hot.

title: peach crisp
directions: Starting with peaches, layer in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325°
for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: fudgy nut squares
directions: In saucepan, combine 3/4 cup oleo and 1/3 cup chocolate chips; stir over low heat until smooth.
Add combined crumbs, coconut and nuts; mix well.
Press onto bottom of ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Chill.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Mix until well blended; spread over crust. Chill.
Melt remaining chocolate chips and oleo; spread over cream cheese layer.
Chill; cut into squares.
Refrigerate.

title: alex's quiche
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Put bread in pan and then add meat or vegetable.
Mix half and half, eggs and dry mustard.
Pour over meat or vegetable.
Sprinkle with cheese. Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, onion, salt and pepper in a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine soup and milk. Pour over potato mixture. Trim fat from pork chops. Brown both sides in a skillet.	Place on top of potato mixture. Cover and bake at 350°
for
hour	and
minutes or until tender. Yields 4 servings.

title: party mix
directions: Mix together and stir into oysterettes and nuts until oil mixture is absorbed by oysterettes.

title: lorain's banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and mashed bananas and beat.
Sift flour and salt.
Combine both mixtures.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: frozen mocha cheesecake
directions: In a small bowl, combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
In a buttered 9-inch spring-form pan or a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, put crumbs firmly on bottom and up sides of pan.
Chill.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add 1 1/2 cup sugar beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks.
Beat on medium-high for 5 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Mix until blended after each addition.
Add chocolate morsels and grated chocolate.
Beat room temperature egg whites, until foamy.
Gradually add remaining 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 25 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Combine powdered sugar and 1 tablespoon milk stirring well, more if needed.
Spoon over warm cake sprinkled with remaining chocolate morsels.

title: boston fish chowder
directions: Cook fish in water with a slice of onion until it flakes (less than 10 minutes).
Drain reserving liquid to cook potatoes.
Dice salt pork and cook in a large pan until some is dried out.
Add sliced onion and saute until soft, but not brown.
Blend flour into pork fat.
Add fish and potato stock.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add milk and bring to a boil again.
Add fish and potatoes; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add clams, juice and shrimp.
Use immediately or refrigerate and reheat when ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup and sour cream.
Add boneless cooked chicken. Make stuffing mix according to directions on box.
Put 1/2 tuffing mix in bottom of 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add chicken mixture. Put remaining 1/2 of stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: oriental pork chops
directions: Combine soy sauce, oil, orange juice, green peppers, brown sugar, ginger and turmeric in bowl; mix well.
Arrange pork chops in shallow dish.
Add marinade.
Marinate, covered, in refrigerator for 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Place pork chops on grill.
Grill for 25 minutes on each side, basting occasionally with reserved marinade.

title: chicken breast diane
directions: Heat 1 Tbsp. each of oil and butter in skillet.
Cook chicken breasts 4 minutes on each side, no longer.
Put on serving platter.
Add spices to pan cook 15 minutes, whisking constantly. Whisk in broth.
Stir until smooth.
Whisk in remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken.

title: frozen pineapple delight
directions: Combine crumbs and melted butter.
Put aside 1/2 cup of buttered crumbs for the top.
Put the rest in 9 x 12-inch pan and press down smoothly.
Cream remaining butter; gradually add icing sugar.
Cream thoroughly.
Add egg until smooth.
Add vanilla flavor, if desired, and spread mixture over crumbs in the pan. Whip cream until stiff.
Combine with tin of pineapple, well drained.
Spread over mixture in pan.
Sprinkle the remaining buttered crumbs over the top and decorate.
Place in freezer and keep it there until needed.
It can be kept for 1 month.
Set out 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: rachel angel's roasted potatoes with garlic and rosemary
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Coat jelly roll pan with oil; add potatoes and remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat.
Bake 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring once 1/2 way through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: "pina colada wedges"(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar and rum until smooth.
Fold in 2 cups of Cool Whip, pineapple with syrup and 2 cups of coconut. Spread in 8-inch layer pan lined with plastic wrap.
Freeze for 2 hours.

title: 3 layer dessert
directions: Mix all together.
Press in 12 x 8-inch pan or baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: pat's macaroni salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: salmon haystacks
directions: Drain liquid from salmon into measuring cup and add milk to make 1/2 cup of liquid.
Melt butter and stir in flour to thicken, then add milk and onion.
Mix into salmon.
Shape into haystacks and roll in crumbs.
Make 3 inch height for dinner servings or 1 1/2-inch height for hors d'oeuvres.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Mix together all other ingredients.
Stir together just until moistened.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full and bake at 400° F. for 20 to 25 minutes. Should make 10 muffins.

title: schubert's special rolls
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients together. Warm buttermilk and melt butter or margarine.

Add margarine and buttermilk to dry mixture. Then add yeast, dissolved in 1/2 cup of lukewarm water; mix well until all dry ingredients are moistened and until dough is blended. Place roll batter on lightly floured surface kneading several times. Shape into large mounds and let rest for 10 minutes. Roll dough out and cut with biscuit cutter. Dip each biscuit in very warm melted butter or margarine and place on baking sheet. Allow to rise and double in size (this can be 30 minutes to 1 hour). Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until outside is golden brown.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Combine with cottage cheese.
Place uncooked lasagna noodles in pan.
Place portion of spinach mixture on noodles.
Pour portion of spaghetti sauce over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat until pan is full.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until noodles are soft.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix together to taste.
Dip fresh fruit in mixture and eat.

title: delicious spinach dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and soup mix together.
Let chill 3 hours before serving.
When ready to serve, squeeze all of the water out of spinach and add to mixture.
Cut a big hole in the center of the bread and fill with mixture.
Cube the piece of bread that you took out of the loaf to use to spoon the mixture onto the pieces of bread.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut in squares, roll in flour and brown in a small amount of shortening.
Put in roasting pan.
Take the mushroom soup and steak sauce and mix in pan.
Heat to a boil. Pour over meat and bake 1 1/2 hours in a 275° oven.
Serves 15.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs. Stir in pineapple and juice. Mix in bread cubes. Looks curdled. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: french fried shrimp in beer batter(serves 6)
directions: Combine ingredients (except shrimp) and beat well.
Split and dry shrimp thoroughly.
Dip into batter and fry in deep fat (oil) at 375° until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper and serve immediately.
Can be used on any fish.
Keep batter chilled until used.

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix butter,
cream
and
flour	thoroughly, then chill. Heat oven to
Divide dough into thirds.
Keep remainder in refrigerator until ready to use.
Roll 1/3 of the dough 1/8 of an inch thick	on
a floured cloth-covered board.
Cut with 1 1/2-inch
round cutter.
Place
rounds on wax paper
that is heavily covered with sugar.
Turn each round with a spatula so each side is coated
with sugar.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Prick each with a
fork
about
times.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes.
Cool.
Put
cookies
together	with this filling. Makes about 5 dozen double cookies (I get less).

title: marinated artichokes
directions: Cut 1/2-inch off bottom of artichokes.
Cut prickers off each leaf.
Boil artichokes in water and cover pan, approximately 20 minutes or when fork stuck in bottom and soft.
Remove from pan.

title: apple-oatmeal cookies(makes 3 dozen cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a medium bowl, combine oats, all-purpose flour, whole-wheat flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir to combine. Stir in raisins and apples. In a large bowl, combine egg, honey, oil and milk. Stir in dry ingredients. Mix to form a smooth batter. Drop batter onto ungreased baking sheets, using a rounded teaspoonful of dough for each cookie, leaving 2-inches between. Dip fingers into water. Press dough down to about 1 1/2-inch diameter. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly golden. Remove from oven. Transfer cookies to cooling rack.

title: zucchini squash relish
directions: Cook until thick; put in containers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the sugar, flour and cocoa in a small container until well blended.
Melt butter in an iron skillet on low heat.
Add the dry ingredients to the butter; mix lightly.
Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Add milk to eggs; beat together.
Add the egg mixture to the dry ingredients in the skillet gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell; cover with meringue.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: town and country chicken
directions: Cube zucchini and chop onion.
Add water and boil together for 15 minutes, drain.
Add remaining ingredients except margarine and stuffing.
Layer 1/2 stuffing mixture on bottom of dish. Then layer all of filling mixture.
Pur remaining stuffing mixture on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crescent roll pizza
directions: Spread rolls out flat on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes. Cool well.

title: chicken in mushroom gravy
directions: Place chicken pieces in crock-pot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix wine or broth with soup.
Pour over chicken.
Add mushrooms.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours (when on high 3 to 4 hours).
Recipe may be doubled for the 5-quart model.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes two loaves.

title: easy chicken bake
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Put chicken, 2 cans soup, noodles and milk in dish.
Combine melted oleo and bread.
Place on top of other ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easy eggplant
directions: Mix dry seasoning, oil, wine and garlic, along with tomato sauce.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Fry eggplant slices.
Put line of eggplant in glass dish; cover with half of cheese.
Put remaining eggplant slices on next.
Pour tomato sauce mixture on top.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: weight watchers vegetable soup
directions: Cook all ingredients until tender.
May add 1 (4-ounce) can mushrooms and/or a 16-ounce can of French-style wax beans.

title: reese's cups
directions: Crush crackers.
Add peanut butter in butter and sugar.
Mix well and shape into balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Mix all together and add 2 bags hand-broken pretzels.
Bake 1 hour at 200°.

title: baked chicken breasts(low-fat)
directions: Remove skin and rinse chicken breasts.
Drain and place in a baking dish.
Cover at least 1/2 way with dressing and cover dish with foil.
Bake at 350° until done and uncover to brown if you like.
Turn 2 or 3 times while baking.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine tomatoes, onion, celery, tomato sauce, water, 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crab rolls
directions: Mix together first nine ingredients.
Remove top third of roll and hollow out inside.
Spoon crab mixture into each roll. Sprinkle with almonds and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Place tops on rolls and bake another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: crunchy green pea salad
directions: Rinse frozen peas in hot water; drain.
Combine peas with vegetables, cashews, bacon and sour cream.
Mix together the dressing and mustard.
Pour over salad.
Toss gently.

title: crab dip
directions: Heat soup.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water and add to soup. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold sprayed with Pam and rinsed with cold water.
Chill 5 hours or until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: swedish heirloom cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
Mix everything together with a fork.
Shape into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: monster cookies
directions: *Add any, or all if you like.

title: glazed onions amandine
directions: Cook onions in lightly salted boiling water until tender. Drain.
In skillet, melt oleo.
Add rest of ingredients and cook slowly, stirring until onions are glazed and lightly browned, about 15 minutes.
Delicious with roast beef or chicken.
I use lemon pepper in this.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: gumbo
directions: Brown in skillet the Crisco and flour.
Add onion, celery, okra and bell pepper.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 quarts of water.
Add tomato paste.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet dough yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: turkey cutlets with peach salsa
directions: Roast peppers.
Remove skin and dice.
In a nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray, saute sliced onions and peppers. Season with 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Place peaches in boiling water for a few minutes.
Peel.
Working over a bowl to collect peach juice, slice or dice peaches.
Mix white wine with peaches and juice. Combine with onions in skillet and cook until liquid is reduced by 1/2.
Serve warm over turkey cutlets which have been grilled, broiled or pan-fried.
Serves 4.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, add ground beef to 1 quart water.
Stir until the beef separates to a fine texture.
Boil slowly 1/2 hour. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hamburger, bacon, beans
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cook ingredients until tender.
Cook 1/2 fryer.
When cool, cut into pieces to make 2 cups.

title: german nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: scotch cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar; set aside.
Bring to a boil, oleo, cocoa and water.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, blend together all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° until sharp bladed knife inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool. Refrigerate.

title: bool go ghi(korean barbecue)
directions: The meat is sliced into pieces of about 1/5 of an inch and 1 square inch in size.
Mix meat and marinate for at least 1/2 hour or overnight. Broil on charcoal fire or in an oven, both sides of meat.
Serve warm with rice.

title: date bars
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl. Add brown sugar and mix well. Add shortening and eggs and mix well.
Stir in nuts, dates and vanilla. Spread in greased 11 x 7-inch or 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
While warm, cut in bars and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: irma's casserole
directions: Drain and wipe chilies dry.
Remove seeds and slice green chilies.
Layer chilies on the bottom of a 9 x 13 baking dish. Add monterey jack cheese.
Combine eggs and sour cream.
Pour mixture over cheese layer.
Bake at 350 F approx. 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: cream coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding milk a little at a time.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 325° until crust is brown.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise, then crosswise into quarters.
Dip pieces into egg, next into Shake 'n Bake mix.
Arrange in greased 9 x 13-inch pan, single layer of zucchini.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until tender.
Top with Mozzarella cheese, then tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and oregano mixture.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Any type fruit desired may be used as topping.
Suggest: strawberries, bananas (soaked in lemon juice), pears, apples, kiwi, grapes, cherries and peaches.

title: jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine with butter and sugar; beat until creamy.
Add jam and beaten egg yolks.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Beat as little as possible. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Cook about 30 minutes or until it tests done with a toothpick.

title: holiday yams
directions: Bake yams; when done, peel and mash.
Add ingredients.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes a good vegetable casserole and it serves a crowd.

title: goody salad
directions: Mix lime Jell-O, lemon Jell-O and hot water well; cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and set in refrigerator.
When thick, cut into squares.
Can be served on lettuce.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Place in crust, then hash browns and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and oregano.
Pour evenly over cheese.
Top with mushrooms or onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 more minutes.
May be garnished with pimento.

title: hamburger cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease two (8 or 9-inch) pie pans.
Cook beef and onion until brown; drain grease.
Add salt and pepper; stir.
Spread mixture into pie pans.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs until smooth.
Pour over meat and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: broccoli-ham soup
directions: Saute ham and garlic in the olive oil, about 3 minutes.
Add tomato, chopped plus juice, stock, thyme, salt and pepper.
Bring to a simmer.
Then add broccoli and pasta and cook until all ingredients are tender, about 20 minutes.
Adjust seasoning. Sprinkle each serving with cheese.

title: sausage stuffed turban squash
directions: Slice bottom stem so squash stands upright.
Cut out top turban end.
Lightly salt inside.
Bake squash; scoop end down in shallow pan with small amount of water at 375° for one hour or until tender.
In skillet, brown sausage and vegetables.
Drain well.
Combine egg, sour cream and Parmesan cheese.
Stir into sausage.
Turn into squash.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes more.

title: steak and rice casserole
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in the boiling water and set aside. Wash uncooked rice. Cut steak into small cubes.

title: poko's cheese ball
directions: Grate mozzarella and cheddar cheese.
Grate hot pepper.
Blend smooth by hand.
Dice green onions, green pepper, and celery.
The smaller the better.
Add diced pimiento and salt to taste.
Add garlic powder and worcestershire.
Blend with cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise and ranch dressing.
Add thousand island or bacon tomato dressing.
Equal parts until smooth.
You will think that it will not harden, but it will when chilled.
Ball up and roll in pecan pieces.
Chill.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Combine all ingredients except oleo and crackers.
Put in greased casserole dish. Crush crackers on top and dot with the whole stick of butter.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 50 minutes. Cook an additional 10 minutes, uncovered. Salt and pepper as needed.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: In double boiler
melt	butter, salt, peanut butter and cocoa. Add vanilla.
Slowly
add	confectioners
sugar
until melted together.
Add
milk
when necessary to soften mixture. Pour onto buttered plate
when mixture is shiny in appearance. Let cool; cut into serving size squares.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Coat casserole dish with margarine.
Cover bottom of casserole with layer of crushed crackers.
Place layer of asparagus (1/2 can) over crackers.
Cover asparagus with a layer of mushroom soup (1/2 can).
Place layer of grated cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients used.
Dot with margarine or butter.
Pour juice from asparagus over top layer.
Bake at 400° approximately 20 to 30 minutes until cheese melts and lightly browns.

title: chicken fiesta
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place potato slices and sauce mix in ungreased baking dish.
Stir in water, milk and chilies.
Place chicken breast on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 5 more minutes until melted.
Can top with chopped tomato if you like.
Chicken breast fillets will also work.
Can double for company.

title: soft sugar-free cookies
directions: Bail
the
fruit
bits, raisins and water until tender. Cool and
add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and chill for
30 minutes.
Drop
by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes and cut lengthwise as for French fries.
Place potatoes in center of a large piece of aluminum foil (double thickness).
Shape foil to form a baking dish.
Dot potatoes with butter; sprinkle with seasonings and cheese.
Pour cream over all. Seal foil and cook over hot coals for one to one and a half hours.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening.
After well mixed, add in the peanut butter; mix well. Stir in salt, vanilla, soda and beaten eggs.

Add flour, mixing well. Chill dough for easier handling. Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie pans. Flatten dough balls with fork. A meat tenderizer utensil works even better and makes a decorative pattern in cookie dough.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
After taking the pans from the oven, let them set a couple of minutes for cookies to firm.
To decorate for holiday season, before baking sprinkle colored sugar on top of dough.

title: stuffed spanish shells
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill.
Roll into balls, size of walnuts.
Dip tops in sugar.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate cake pudding
directions: Sift 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt together into 9-inch square baking pan.
Stir in milk, margarine and vanilla; spread evenly into pan.
Combine in bowl 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa and sprinkle over batter.
Pour water over top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Serve as a dip with chips or vegetables or spread on crackers.

title: noel cookie gems
directions: Combine first four ingredients and set aside.
Sift together next four ingredients.
Add to shortening mixture alternately with sour cream, mixing well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls and roll in nuts.
Place 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Press thumb in center of each cookie and fill with jam.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400° or until lightly brown.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli without salt; drain.
Place broccoli in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, milk and egg.
Pour over broccoli.
Mix melted butter and bread crumbs.
Top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: amish cinnamon bread
directions: Place starter in a large bowl.
Add oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Combine soda, baking powder, flour, instant pudding, flour and cinnamon.
(Leave out soda and baking powder if using self-rising flour.)
Add to starter mixture.
Mix by hand using wooden spoon.
Add pecans, apples and raisins.
Mix well. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° approximately 1 hour.

title: lane's baked spaghetti
directions: Brown the ground beef, sausage and pepperoni together.
Add onion and green pepper. Cook until tender. Add spaghetti sauce and spices. Simmer on low temperature for 30 minutes. Add cooked spaghetti and mix well.
Pour sauce and spaghetti into a baking pan.
Put cheese on top and bake in oven for 15 minutes until cheese melts. Feeds 15 people.

title: no name cake
directions: Mix all of these and then stir in 1 can of coconut pecan frosting. Mix well. Pour in oiled Bundt cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Makes 2 cups.

title: walking salad(method:  fireless)
directions: Wash and core apples, saving top of core to use as a lid.
In medium size bowl, mix together the cream cheese, nuts and raisins. Fill apple centers with mixture.
Cover with top of apple core; secure in place with two round wooden toothpicks.
If using as a snack on a hike, put apple in a plastic sandwich bag.

title: raspberry crisp
directions: Crush 1 cup raspberries; add enough water to measure 1 cup.

title: 3 bean hot dish
directions: Brown
hamburger and bacon.
Add all other ingredients. Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: galliano cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat about 5 minutes. Pour into greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack; remove from pan after 20 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar or vanilla glaze when cool.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush cookies and put 1/2 of crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth; mix in powdered sugar.
Fold in whipped cream or topping.
In separate bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Fold cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture together.
Pour into pan on cookie crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook last 6 ingredients over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture turns clear.
Remove from heat; add berries.
Pour into pie shell.
Cool.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: chocolate chip banana muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt in bowl.
In second bowl, mix peanut butter, eggs, sugar, bananas.
Add flour mixture to banana mixture and stir until smooth.
Add chocolate chips and mix.
Scoop into mini muffin pan and bake 385 for 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 48 muffins.
Should be eaten 12 at a time!!

title: chippies
directions: Place graham crackers on Teflon cookie sheet.
In heavy saucepan, bring oleo, butter and sugar to boil and cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Spread over graham crackers and top with chopped nuts or coconut and chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool before storing.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar icing.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, bread crumbs and eggs.
Form into balls.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Turn once.

title: picante dip
directions: Mix and use as dip with Bugles.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Blend well, then mix into shredded cabbage and let sit a while before serving.

title: ice cream
directions: Heat 3 cups milk; combine eggs, sugar, flour and evaporated milk and pour into warmed milk.
Cook until sugar is dissolved. Let cool, then add remaining 3 cups of milk and vanilla.

title: cheddar apple bread
directions: Cream butter.
Add eggs.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in apples and cheese.
Turn into well greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until well browned.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Put on bottom of pan and spread taco sauce on top.
Layer onions, lettuce and cheese.

title: meat ring
directions: Use leftover roast, fully cooked.
Grind in food processor with onion.
(Can add other seasonings to taste.)

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon; remove bones and skin.
Blend well together the salmon and cream cheese.
Roll in ball over walnuts; refrigerate. Serve with your choice of crackers.
"Great for holidays."

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix strawberry Jell-O by instructions on box.
Put in refrigerator until halfway set.
Then stir in pineapple.
Let set. Then mix whipping cream and put on top of Jell-O mixture.

title: pineapple jello salad
directions: Bring pineapple (juice and all) and sugar to a boil.
Add Jell-O and water.
After Jell-O starts to thicken, add cheese, nuts and toppings.
Chill until set.
Recipe makes a lot!

title: small pancakes(lapper)
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Let rest 1 hour before cooking.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix the oil, sugar, white vinegar, salt and celery seed and boil 2 minutes.
Pour the hot dressing over the vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Overnight is best.

title: honey glazed turkey
directions: Rinse turkey inside and out.
Pat dry.
Reserve giblets and neck for broth.
Make filling.

title: breaded ranch chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine cornflakes, parmesan cheese and ranch mix.
Dip chicken in butter, then roll in cornflake mixture to coat.
Place in a 13x9 inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30-45 minutes or until chicken juices run clear. 4-6 servings.

title: batter rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Spoon this batter into greased muffin tins and bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
This batter will keep in refrigerator.
Keep it well covered.

title: vanilla cake frosting
directions: Combine sugar, Crisco and flavorings.
Mix.
Add milk as needed.

title: orange slice candy cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in 1 egg at a time. Add vanilla.
Mix dates, candy, nuts and coconut with 1/4 cup of flour.
Sift remaining ingredients.
Alternately fold into creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Fold in fruit/nut mixture.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 2 hours.
Remove cake from oven.

title: jalapeno cornbread casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix corn meal, milk, eggs, corn, beans, salt, soda and oil.
Mix well. Batter will be thin.
In a large iron skillet, cook the ground beef and drain.
In a separate large bowl, combine meat, onion, green pepper, garlic, jalapenos and grated cheese.
Pour 1/2 the batter into a well-greased 10 x 12-inch cast-iron skillet. Spread filling evenly over batter. Pour remaining batter over the filling. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: american apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Pare, core and slice apples.
Toss with sugar mixture.
Turn into pastry lined 9-inch pie plate.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust, seal and flute edge.
Cut slits for escape of steam.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes, until pie is desired brownness and apples are tender.

title: venison roast
directions: Brown the roast in hot oil in a roasting pan and season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle the onion soup mix on the meat and add 1/2 cup water.
Bake, covered, at 300° until tender.

title: michigan hard candy
directions: Cook to 300°
on candy thermometer.
Take off and add coloring (red, green or yellow) and 1 teaspoon flavoring.
Pour on large cookie sheet.
Cut in small pieces with scissors before completely cool.
Mix with powdered sugar.
Some different flavors you may use are oil of lemon, orange, peppermint, anise, raspberry, grape, wintergreen, etc.
These oils are available at Walgreen's.
The oils are better than the imitation flavorings found in grocery stores.

title: coney island hot dog sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain well and add rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer until well blended.
Makes 2 cups or enough for 10 hot dogs.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Grind mushrooms and onion together and simmer in 1 cup of water with bouillon cubes until tender.
Add milk and butter, salt and pepper.

title: cheesecake brownies
directions: Slice 1 roll of cookie dough and place cookies close together in the bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch dish.
(Place other roll in the freezer until ready to use).
When dough in the dish is softened, press into pan with spoon until bottom is covered. Combine next 4 ingredients in medium mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Pour mixture over cookie dough in dish.
Slice remaining roll of dough and place slices close together on top of filling. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until cream is lightly browned.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with cornflakes and drizzle butter over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 12.

title: hard tack candy
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients together to hard crack stage (300°).
Remove from heat and add flavoring and coloring.
Pour onto a lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Score and then cool. Break and cut into pieces.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: southern granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large glass dish.
Heat honey, oil, molasses and vanilla until blended.
Drizzle over dry mix.
Heat at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool before storing in sealed container in refrigerator.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: In small bowl, combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and margarine until well blended.
Spread one-fourth of mixture on one slice of ham; repeat with remaining cheese mixture and ham slices. Roll up from short sides; chill for several hours or wrap and freeze, if desired.
To serve, slice rolls into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Arrange slices on top of Ritz crackers.
If frozen, let stand at room temperature 20 minutes before serving.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen appetizers.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Mix in saucepan cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, enchilada sauce and taco sauce.
Layer 2-quart casserole dish.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Combine water and cornstarch; add salt, brown sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce.
Cook until thick.
Add green pepper, onion and pineapple.
Brown the chicken in oil.
Cover with sauce.
Bake at 325° until tender.
Serves 6.

title: temptations
directions: Cream together butter and peanut butter.
Add sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Roll into approximately 1-inch balls and place in tassie pans.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: In large saucepan, heat oil.
Saute onion, garlic and green pepper until tender.
Add ground round, salt and pepper.
Cook until meat is done and drain well.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, oregano and parsley.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until sauce has thickened.
While cooking, if sauce becomes too thick, add a small amount of water.

title: mexican salad
directions: Place each ingredient in a separate bowl and build your own salad.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and sugar together; add other ingredients and mix well.
Cook on hot oiled grill or skillet.

title: dill spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Puree with remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Yields 3 1/4 cups. One-forth cup equals 35 calories and 0 grams fat.

title: cranberry-cherry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except milk.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: chuck roast in foil
directions: Place roast on foil.
Spread on mushroom soup; sprinkle on onion soup.
Wrap loosely in foil.
Bake for 4 to 5 hours at 350°.

title: pecan-peanut roll
directions: Combine
sugars, syrup, vinegar and milk in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook to soft-ball state, 236° on a candy thermometer.
Cool
to
room
temperature,
then
beat
until creamy.
Add the peanut butter and stir until blended.
Dust a board
with
confectioners
sugar and turn candy out on to it. Knead
candy
and
shape
into
one
or two rolls.
Cover with chopped pecans.
Cool and slice when firm.

title: laurine's chicken salad
directions: Boil hen in water with bay leaf, celery stalk, salt and pepper.
When hen is done, cool it, then remove all skin and bones from meat.
Add chopped eggs, mayonnaise and sweet pickles.

title: hidden valley pretzels
directions: Combine spices and Hidden Valley mix with the oil.
Place pretzel pieces on a baking sheet.
Pour oil mixture over pretzels and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Cool on paper towels.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and cook on medium-low heat for 1 hour.
Serve with cornbread or soda crackers.

title: honey beans with cheddar cheese
directions: Saute bacon and onion; drain grease.
Pour into oblong baking dish.
Add pork and beans, sugar, ketchup and honey to bacon and onion.
Mix well.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Don't try to cook at higher temperature, it will melt the cheese!

title: carrot orange soup
directions: Saute carrots and onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Add stock and bay leaf, cook 20 minutes or until carrots are soft.
Puree mixture, return to pan, add mandarin juice, ginger and salt and pepper to taste.
Reheat, garnish with mint and mandarin peel. Serves 2.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar and beer well.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour butter over top and cook 10 minutes more or until brown.
Best when eaten warm.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Add eggs and mix.
Add brown sugar, butter, salt and cinnamon; mix.
Smooth out and put pecans on top. Mix 3/4 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup melted butter; add on top of pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 45 minutes, or until desired brownness.
Let cool for a few minutes so topping will be crunchy.

title: deviled ham and cheese rolls
directions: Stir together and mix well the first four ingredients.
Split rolls and fill with mixture.
Put tops on rolls and place back in foil pan.
Cover with foil and heat at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two bread pans.
Blend shortening and sugar until fluffy.
(Oil is fine if you don't have solid shortening.)
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Mix in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and spices.
Add walnuts. Pour into pans and bake for one hour.
After removing pans from oven, set pans on side to cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in 9 x 13 casserole dish. Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes. Mix corn flakes and 1/4 c. butter and pour on top. Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine corn meal, flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
In a second bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Add to dry ingredients and stir only enough to moisten.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and tests done.

title: corn pudding for fifty
directions: Thaw corn.
Combine corn and all ingredients except egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold into corn mixture.
Pour into two 12 x 20 x 2-inch baking pans.
Place in pans of hot water.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: polvorones(wedding cookies)
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Gradually add flour, soda and anise.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut or smaller.
Grease cookie pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Yield:
100 cookies.

title: banana split cheese cake
directions: Mix crackers, margarine (melted) and 1/4 cup sugar. Press into 13 x 9 pan. Mix cheese, remaining 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla with mixer until blended. Add eggs. Mix. Stir in banana. Pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight. Top with strawberries (I use frozen), sliced banana and pineapple. Sprinkle with chopped pecans and drizzle with chocolate.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.

title: grater tater casserole
directions: Spray a large dish with Pam and melt 2/3 stick margarine.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Then grate 4 ounces of sharp cheese and put over potatoes; bake 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: golden citrus punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale and freeze in gallon containers.
Remove from freezer and thaw approximately 2 hours before serving.
Chop mixture in separate bowl, then place in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and serve.

title: cranberry-walnut cabbage slaw
directions: In small bowl, mix mayonnaise, pickle relish, honey mustard, honey, pepper, celery seed and salt. In large bowl, combine cabbage, walnuts, celery, onion, sweet red pepper and cranberries. Add mayonnaise mixture to cabbage and toss to coat. Cover and chill at least 1 hour or up to 6 hours. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: working parent's overnight lasagna
directions: Break noodles in half; set aside.
Stir herbs into cottage cheese.
Reserve 1/2 cup Mozzarella.
Spread enough sauce on bottom of deep 8 or 9-inch square pan to cover entire surface. Cover with 1/3 of noodles, breaking and overlapping to fit. Spread 1/2 of cottage cheese over noodles.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of remaining Mozzarella and 1/3 of remaining sauce.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Uncover; bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Top with reserved Mozzarella and bake 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: fruit filled bar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine oleo, sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Beat until fluffy.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in greased jelly roll pan.
Spread pie filling over dough. Top with remaining dough.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: clam stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Remove and dice mushroom stems.
Dip caps in butter and place, rounded side down, on a rack on a cookie sheet.
Drain clams and reserve liquid.
In melted butter, saute mushroom stems and garlic.
Add clam liquid and simmer until mushroom stems are tender. Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients. Spoon mixture into mushroom caps.
Broil about 6-inches from heat for about 8 minutes until mushrooms are tender and tops are lightly browned. Sprinkle a few drops of lemon juice on each and serve hot.

title: wasp nest cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed with milk.
Let cool slightly.
Mix with the cake mix.
Put in baking dish or pan.
Spread nuts, butterscotch chips and coconut.
Pour over top of cake and bake at 350° or until done.

title: oven roasted sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees. Grease baking pan. Cut sweet potatoes crosswise into 3/4 slices, halving larger sweet potatoes if necessary. Place in a single layer greased pan. In a small bowl combine oil, honey, rosemary and salt. Microwave on high for 20-30 seconds or until heated. Blend well. Brush mixture over sweet potatoes slices. Bake 425 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until sweet potatoes are tender.

title: cinnamon bun
directions: Grease a Bundt or tube pan and sprinkle nuts and raisins on bottom.
Put in frozen rolls.
Mix brown sugar and pudding. Sprinkle over rolls.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on teaspoon.
Melt margarine and pour over all.
Cover well and leave sitting out all night.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Turn out of pan while warm.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Break Twinkies in half and cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Drain pineapple and spread on Twinkies.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Spread over pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and soda 3 times.
Mix all ingredients.
Roll on floured board.
Cut with cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
I spray cookie sheets.
Drop dough by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Using flat-bottomed cup or glass, dip the cup in saucer of sugar, "stamping" each cookie "lump" flat.
Dip again. "Stamp" another cookie (quicker than rolling).
Allow dough to sit about 20 minutes before baking.
Cookies raise nicer.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes at 340° or store; freeze well between wax paper (so they don't stick together).

title: pizza fondue
