directions: Crumble beef in 2-quart casserole.
Add onion and microwave 5 minutes, stirring once halfway through cooking time.
Drain off fat.
Add cornstarch and seasonings to pizza sauce; stir well. Add to meat.
Microwave 4 minutes.
Combine cheeses and add to sauce mixture 1/3 at a time, microwaving 1 minute after each addition.
Stir well.
Serve with bread cubes.
(Reheat as necessary, or serve in fondue pot or chafing dish).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rye bread
directions: Let raise.
Make into loaves (4 to 5).
Raise, double in size. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Blend all the ingredients together.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Mix by hand; do not use electric mixer.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar and set aside.
Boil oleo, cocoa and water.
Pour this mixture over the flour mixture.
Mix.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: susan's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done; let cool slightly.
Pull from bones and cut into pieces and place into a square 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients (except corn flakes) and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave 16 minutes, stirring after every 4 minutes and rotating dish on all 4 sides.
Let stand about 5 minutes and garnish top with crushed corn flakes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: luscious peach pie
directions: Sprinkle
sugar over peaches.
Let stand 10 minutes; drain. Beat cream cheese at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and almond extract; beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and peaches.
Spoon into graham cracker crust; chill until firm. Yield one 9 inch pie.

title: beef salad
directions: If necessary, cover with spread of mayonnaise and refrigerate.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together and alternate with milk.
Fold in blueberries.
Put into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: delicious drumsticks
directions: Heat the oven to 425°.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper in a bowl.
Dip chicken drumsticks into margarine; roll in flour mixture to coat.
Arrange in an ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Bake, uncovered, until done, about 50 minutes.
Makes 6 drumsticks.

title: peach marmalade
directions: Simmer lemons and orange slices until tender, about 20 minutes.
Place in a 4-cup measure.
Peel and chop peaches.
Add to lemon and orange slices until the 4-cup measure is full.
Place fruit in a large heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add Sure-Jell and margarine.
Add sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Skim.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Process in hot water bath 10 minutes.
Makes 7 1/2 pints.

title: upside down vegetable pizza
directions: If using tomato sauce, add basil, oregano and garlic.
Brown turkey.
Layer in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer any vegetables (cooked a little on stove) on top of turkey.
Layer 2 cups sauce on top of veggies.
Put a little cheese on top.
Place the crescent rolls on top as a crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix soup and sour cream together; spread over chicken.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour melted margarine over cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until bubbly.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions, then add seasonings.
Arrange meat, potatoes and string beans in layers.
Put catsup on top.
Brown in oven.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and butter together; bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, salt and cream of tartar.
Mix well.
Quickly pour over corn.
Mix well and put in greased roaster pan.
(Do not cover.)
Bake in 200° oven 1 hour. Stir 3 to 4 times during baking.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Wash and peel potatoes.
Heat the milk to almost boiling. Slice potatoes into thin discs and layer into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
On each layer, sprinkle two tablespoons of flour and 1/4 teaspoon of salt and pepper.
Pour heated milk over all layers.
Dot with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: popcorn surprise
directions: Place popcorn in microwave for 3 to 4 minutes or until it stops popping.
Place popcorn in a bowl and then add Doritos and Chee-tos. Stir until satisfied.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Melt chips and sweetened condensed milk together over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into cake pan and put in refrigerator for one hour, then cut into cake-like pieces.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until brown.
Set aside. Cook broccoli.
Set aside.
Cook rice.
Add cheese whiz to hot rice and add mushroom soup.
Add onions and celery.
Add cooked broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add a touch more orange juice if mix is too stiff.
Serve with fresh fruits.

title: baked stuffed squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Halve and clean squash.
Brush insides with oil.
Place in baking dish with 1/4-inch of water.
Set in oven to bake for 45 minutes.
Prepare stuffing by cooking onion in oil until clear.
Add sunflower seeds and stir 1 minute more.
Add salt, herbs, soy sauce and water.
Reduce heat to low and simmer uncovered 5 to 10 minutes.
Add rice or breadcrumbs.
Fill squash after 45 minutes and cook for 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: double boiler bread pudding
directions: Place in top of double boiler, sugar on top of this and place slice of bread, buttered.
Pour over this the beaten eggs and milk, salt and vanilla.
Do not stir.
The sugar makes the sauce. Cook 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, green and red pepper in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and cover with cold water.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Press out excess liquid.

title: marinated rump roast
directions: Marinate overnight.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour per pound.
Baste during cooking.

title: hot crab appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove cartilage from crabmeat. Combine remaining ingredients and mix gently with crabmeat. Spoon into a casserole and bake 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: peaches and cream cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and sides of 9 inch deep dish pie pan.
After combining above ingredients, pour into prepared pan.
Place over batter one can (15-20 oz.) sliced peaches, well drained.
Reserve juice.
Combine in small bowl and beat at medium speed 8 oz. softened cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, 3 Tbsp. reserved juice.
Spoon this mixture to within one inch of side of pie dish - if it touches side of dish, it will cook over.
Sprinkle cinnamon over cream cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 -35 minutes until crust is golden.
Filling will appear soft.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Boil sugar, water, vinegar, salt, pepper and oil for 5 minutes.
Pour over vegetables, onions and pimentos.
Place overnight in the refrigerator.

title: mini ham sandwiches
directions: In small saucepan combine butter, onion flakes, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and poppy seed.
Heat until butter is melted and mix well.
Slice dinner rolls.
Make sandwiches with ham and cheese.
After making sandwiches, replace in foil roll pans.
Pour butter mixture over rolls.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut rolls into individual sandwiches.
Yields 4 dozen sandwiches.

title: garden style swirls
directions: Cut vegetables in desired sizes and pour dressing over. Sprinkle on cheese.
Chill before serving.
Makes a large quantity.

title: cranberry-strawberry salad
directions: Mix together; chill in refrigerator.

title: turkey rose
directions: Remove bread crusts and butter bread on both sides.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spray mayonnaise on 1 side of cheese and place, mayonnaise side down, on bread.
Beat eggs with milk.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Mix soups together (no diluting) and pour over eggs.
Sprinkle with pimento.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put in fridge in bowl and cover.
Enjoy.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix together mashed potatoes, to which butter has already been included when mashing of the potatoes, salt, pepper, garlic powder, minced onion and cornmeal (just enough to achieve right consistency) and eggs.
Spoon drop potatoes in hot oil and brown on both sides.
Serve hot!!

title: nicoise green beans
directions: Saute onion and celery in large frying pan with the oil until lightly browned.
Boil or steam beans until tender (about 10 minutes).
Drain and set aside.
Add tomatoes, stock, juice or water, bay leaf, parsley and other spices to saute.
Stir well and simmer for 20 minutes, uncovered.
Continue to season to taste. Add the cooked beans to the sauce and stir.
Bring to a simmer and cook for 2 to 3 more minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serve with pasta, rice or potatoes.

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, using an electric mixer, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy; beat in egg.
Reduce mixer to low speed and beat in flour mixture, oats and rind.
Stir in the raisins.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheets two inches apart.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: broccoli-cheddar cheese casserole
directions: Butter an 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Cover bottom of dish generously with torn bite-size pieces of bread.
Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces and lay on top of bread pieces.
Mix together all remaining ingredients.
Pour over broccoli and bread. Cover dish with foil or glass cover and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Soak sliced eggplant in water (removes bitterness); saute in oil.
Mix bread, Romano cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and garlic in bowl.
In casserole, add layer of eggplant slices, mixed bread cubes, Mozzarella cheese and tomato sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spice dip
directions: Mix sugar with spices.
Fold into whipped topping.
Garnish with additional cinnamon, if desired.
Store in refrigerator.
Use to dip cookies, cake cubes, fresh fruit or pretzel sticks.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.
Only 6 calories per teaspoon.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach, pressing out as much liquid as possible.
Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Place in container with wax paper between layers. Freeze.
When ready to use, place frozen balls on cookie sheet and bake at 350 for 15 minutes.

title: lemon cheese filling
directions: Mix and cook over low heat for 12 minutes.
Cool and frost 3 layer cake.

title: baked key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until smooth.
Blend in sweetened condensed milk.
Add Key lime juice gradually.
Pour into baked and cooled pastry shell.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until set; usually 10 to 12 minutes.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form when beater is lifted.
Add sugar gradually, beating to soft peaks.
Spread meringue on warm filling.
Bake 20 minutes or until meringue has golden peaks.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: five hour oven stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 4-quart casserole or Dutch oven. Cover and cook at 250° for 5 hours, stirring once or twice. (Ingredients and quantities can be varied to your liking.)
This can be prepared ahead of time but not frozen.
Serves 6.

title: corn chowder
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion, celery and garlic.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add 4 cups of corn kernels and chicken stock.
Bring to a boil.
Once boiling, lower heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: texas style swiss steak
directions: Dip meat in flour, salt, pepper and mustard mixed together. Brown pieces in oil.
Place in a casserole.
Scatter cut-up vegetables over the top of the meat.
Pour sauce of catsup and brown sugar over all.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: kahlua number 2
directions: Boil sugar and water until clear, about 5 minutes.
While hot, add powdered instant coffee.
Cool.
Put into gallon jug.
Add fifth of cheap booze and 2 vanilla beans split lengthwise.
Let stand for 2 weeks or more.
Filter and bottle.
Serve in little glasses.
Keep vanilla beans and add only 1 bean to next brew.

title: broken glass torte
directions: Prepare the orange, cherry and lime gelatins separately, using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cold water for each.
Chill overnight or until firm.
Mix pineapple juice and sugar; heat until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve the lemon gelatin in this hot juice.
Add the remaining 1/2 cup cold water to this mixture; chill until slightly thick.
Mix crumbs and butter; press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Increase crumbs and butter mix if you want to cover the sides and top with crumbs.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Put ground beef in aluminum foil.
Add other ingredients. Bring foil up like a hobo bag.
Bake until done.
Drain.
Serve with bun and salad.

title: tuna tofu
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into patties and fry until brown.

title: sparkling harvest cider
directions: In punch bowl, combine cider, lemon juice and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Garnish with apple slices and cinnamon sticks.
Serve over ice.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: good barbecue
directions: Do not use cast-iron skillet.
Lightly brown onion in small amount of oil, then crumble in hamburger and cook until done. Drain and add soup, Worcestershire sauce, ketchup, garlic salt, pepper and thyme.
Makes enough for 10 to 12 small hamburger buns.
If making for large group, do not double.
Start over.

title: hal's wassail
directions: Pour juice in a 12-cup percolator.
Place sliced orange, cinnamon stick and red hots in basket and perk.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and beat well.
Fold in the remaining ingredients.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Butter pie pan first.

title: picnic beans
directions: Drain butter and kidney beans. Mix all beans together. Add hamburger. Add diced bacon, onion and tomatoes. Spread brown sugar over top and bake at 325° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: peach or apple cobbler
directions: Batter:
Combine flour, salt and baking powder. Stir in sugar, milk and melted butter.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the butter, water and peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Add flour, sugar and salt.
Beat in eggs, sour cream and baking soda.
Pour into a greased and floured 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Icing should be made while the cake is baking.

title: reduced fat garlic bread
directions: Split French loaf (if I am cooking for myself, a slice or two of regular loaf bread will do).
Spray loaf with butter flavor cooking spray.
Add garlic powder or garlic salt.
Toast bread or let it heat in oven.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: date nut roll
directions: Crush crackers.
Place on waxed paper.
Leave 1/2 cup for mixing with other ingredients.
Cut dates, marshmallows and pecans into small pieces.
Add milk until well blended.
Add 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Pour on crushed cracker crumbs and form long roll.
Place in waxed paper in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chuck wagon surprise
directions: Saute hamburger, onion and bell pepper; drain.
Cook macaroni. Combine all ingredients and simmer until good and hot.
Good served with garlic bread and salad.

title: buffet potato casserole
directions: Combine hash browns and oleo.
Season with salt and pepper. Blend all ingredients and pour into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix 2 cups crushed corn flakes with 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: casserole cookie
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar gradually, beating until fluffy. Stir in rest of ingredients. Put in 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove and stir well. Let cool and form into balls. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: o'henrietta bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand in fridge about 1 hour to soak up flavor.
Add chopped pepperoni for flavor.

title: lemon coleslaw salad
directions: Make jello; add other ingredients.

title: orange glazed pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops lightly with salt and pepper; dredge in flour.
Heat oil in a heavy skillet, brown chops on both sides. Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well; pour over chops. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet carrots
directions: Steam carrots in microwave to the consistency you prefer. Toss with lemon juice, Equal, brown sugar and cinnamon.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal jumbo
directions: About 2 hours before serving or up to 2 weeks ahead, mix ingredients together.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease large cookie sheet.
Into large bowl, measure all ingredients except oats. With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until well blended, occasionally scraping bowl with spatula.
With wooden spoon, stir in oats until well mixed.
Drop half of dough by heaping tablespoonfuls, about 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes and onions with water.
Cook until tender. Mash.
Add powdered milk, bouillon, 2 cups water, celery powder and onion powder.
Add salt to taste.
Bring up to temperature and serve.

title: rye boat
directions: Mix all the ingredients except bread together.
Take the rye bread
and scoop out the middle, saving the little pieces for the dip.
After the ingredients are all mixed together, when ready to serve, scoop dip into the bread.

title: suet pudding sauce
directions: Mix all but the butter and vanilla in a saucepan.
Cook until clear.
Remove from fire and add the butter and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: texas star mexican soup
directions: Sort and rinse beans. Soak overnight, and drain.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Add all other ingredients (except corn).
Heat and pour into casserole dish. Cover with corn and bread mixture.

title: smashed sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Scrub the potatoes; prick them several times with a knife or fork and bake them for 1 hour or until very soft when pierced with a knife. Remove from the oven and as soon as they are cool enough to handle, scoop out the insides. Place the sweet potato meat into the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment and add the orange juice, cream, butter, brown sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and pepper. Mix together until combined, but not smooth. Transfer into a baking dish. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes until heated through. Serves 8.

title: meat and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles by directions on package; drain.
In a large frying pan, fry sausage and beef until brown; stir often.
Add onion, pepper and mushrooms; cook about 3 minutes.
Drain off excess fat.
Add salt, pizza sauce and noodles; stir just enough to mix.
Pour into a large greased bake dish.
Place pepperoni on meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased angel food cake pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Crush 1 cup blueberries and add to 1 cup water in saucepan. Stir in cornstarch, sugar and lemon juice.
Cook on medium heat until mixture is clear and thick.
Cool.
Add to remaining berries.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell. Chill and top with whipped cream.

title: jay's chili
directions: In Dutch oven, saute first four ingredients in hot oil until tender.
Add meat, 1 pound at a time, stirring until meat loses redness.
Drain; add water.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring after each addition.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring frequently. Season to taste with garlic, salt and pepper, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Serve with Pillsbury cornbread twists.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.

Beat eggs until light and fluffy. Add milk, cream, sugar and salt. Stir in corn, bread crumbs and butter and place dish in pan of boiling water. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until custard is set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soups and milk.
In 3-quart dish, layer chicken and soup.
Put dressing on top.
Pour broth over dressing.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: corn relish
directions: Boil corn-on-the-cob 10 minutes. Cut off and measure 8 cups. Mix celery, peppers, onions, sugar, corn, vinegar, salt and celery seed. Boil 15 minutes. Combine mustard, flour and water.
Mix all ingredients. Boil 5 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Seal at once.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and cranberries;
stir.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold.

title: fudgie chocolate dessert
directions: Mix cake mix in hot cooked pudding.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: can can chicken (number 1)
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture of soup and milk over chicken.
Prepare stuffing mix using package instructions.
Spread over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: california skillet
directions: Heat oil in large skillet. Add beef and onion; cook. Stir in chili powder and other ingredients, except cheese. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and cover.
Cook just until cheese melts.

title: cream cheese cupcakes(from 1975 edition)
directions: Beat cream cheese and eggs together until creamy (they will be lumpy).
Add 1 cup sugar and vanilla and beat.
Pour into 18 cupcake papers (double papers).
Bake for 45 minutes at 325° to 350° on top shelf of oven.
Remove and let center of cakes fall. Fill the hole in center with 1 cup sour cream and 1/2 cup sugar, mixed together.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Top with any fruit pie filling.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup.
Add gelatin and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Beat mayonnaise and cream cheese until smooth.
Add celery, onion and soup mix.
Fold in shrimp.
Pour into a 1-quart mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix; marinate 24 hours before serving.

title: artichoke and chicken casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter until golden brown; set aside.
Put chicken breasts in simmering chicken broth in a single layer.
Cover.
Cook 20 minutes.
Remove from broth.
Save 3/4 cup broth.
Cook, skin and bone chicken.
Arrange chicken slightly overlapping in 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Top with artichoke hearts. Set aside.
Melt 1/4 cup butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in 3/4 cup chicken broth and half and half.
Cook and stir as mixture boils and thickens.
Blend in Parmesan cheese, sherry and rosemary.
Pour over artichokes, covering them.
Sprinkle mushrooms down center.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
You can assemble this ahead of time.
Cover and refrigerate and bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Blend with paprika.
Brown chicken on all sides.
Add broth and simmer 40 minutes.
Dissolve starch in water and blend with yogurt.
Stir yogurt into chicken mixture and heat through.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: turkey tacos(makes 12 servings)
directions: Brown turkey meat lightly in skillet; drain off fat.
Add salad dressing mix, chili powder and tomato sauce; mix well. Simmer 5 to 6 minutes.
Spoon into taco shells, allowing about 1/3 cup for each.

title: crunchy toffee
directions: Butter a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Spread nuts on bottom of pan. Cream butter and sugar over heat and bring to a boil for 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Spread over nuts.
Sprinkle morsels over the top and spread to melt.
Put cookie sheet over the top to hold in the heat to melt morsels.
While warm, cut in squares; then chill until firm.

title: homemade baked beans
directions: Chop and brown bacon with the onion.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Gallon cans of beans bought are the best.
For dried beans, soak and cook before adding to other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for an hour or longer.

title: fresh apple-turkey salad
directions: Combine the diced apples and turkey in a bowl.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Toss lightly; then add celery, eggs, almonds and chives.

title: macpherson scotchcakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour; mix well.
Put dough in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour until brown on top.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: whip cream icing
directions: Cook first 2 ingredients on top of the stove until boiling and thickness occurs, stirring constantly.
Refrigerate to cool.
In separate bowl, mix thoroughly last 3 ingredients.
Combine all ingredients and mix on high speed for 2 minutes.

title: french fried deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise and remove yolks.
Season yolks to taste with Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, pepper, oil and vinegar. Pack back into whites and hold together with toothpicks.
Dip eggs into 2 beaten egg yolks, then flour and bread crumbs.
Fry in deep fat until brown.
Drain eggs on brown paper.
Remove toothpicks.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add uncooked macaroni.
Stir until butter coats macaroni.
Cut cheese slices in quarters.
Add salt, pepper, cheese and cold milk to macaroni.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Comes out of oven creamy and golden brown.
Do not stir while baking.

title: m&m brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and baking soda in a small bowl. Melt butter in a small pan.
Stir in brown sugar and cool.
Pour into large bowl and stir in egg and vanilla.
Beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in half of M&M's.

title: lemon sauce for fish
directions: Melt butter. Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually stir in milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth. Add lemon juice and parsley. Serve over fish.

title: fudge cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Bring to a boil, shortening, oleo, water and cocoa.
Pour in flour-sugar mixture.
While hot, add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Bake in a large shallow pan for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: 4-day coconut cake
directions: First Day:
Mix coconut, sugar and sour cream.
Refrigerate overnight.
Second Day:
Make cake in 2 layers.
Let cool; slice horizontally, making 4 layers.
Ice cake with the coconut mixture. Cake is best if refrigerated for 1 to 2 days, but not necessary.

title: four stack dessert
directions: First Layer: Melt oleo in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Mix the nuts, flour and sugar and press in bottom of pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: elbow macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients while macaroni and eggs are still warm. We like a dash of garlic salt.
Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: boiled chocolate icing
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Stir over medium heat for 1 minute.
Cool.
Add vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread on cake layers.
Will ice 4 layers.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Spread chopped artichoke hearts in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Squeeze excess water from uncooked spinach and spread over artichokes.

title: sesame-garlic cheese spread
directions: Place sesame seed in a small frying pan over medium heat; cook, stirring often, until golden.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Beat in Ricotta or cottage cheese, parsley, garlic salt and the sesame seed.
Mound in a small serving bowl; cover and chill as long as 1 week.
Before serving, let stand at room temperature about half an hour.
Serve the cheese spread with raw vegetables.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy party punch
directions: Dissolve 1/4 cup cinnamon candies in water before adding other ingredients.
Before serving, add 1 quart ginger ale.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Don't open oven.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream shortening and cream cheese.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add egg, vanilla and dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll in balls. Flatten with fork on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake until slightly browned.
(Works well in a cookie press also.)

title: italian salad
directions: Toss first 6 ingredients together.
Mix dressing according to package directions.
Chill.
Pour dressing over salad before serving.

title: parmesan vegetable toss
directions: In a large bowl, break broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Combine with onion.
In small bowl, combine sugar, cheese, salt, basil and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Toss veggies and dressing.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Just before serving, add bacon, lettuce, croutons and water chestnuts.
Toss lightly.
Makes 20 to 24 servings (210 calories).

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Flake salmon and mix with other ingredients.
May be shaped into ball or log and rolled in chopped pecans or parsley.
Wrap in waxed paper or plastic wrap and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: mock cherry pie(cranberry and raisin)
directions: Mix together everything and slowly bring to a boil.
Boil gently 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into 8-inch pie shell (uncooked) and add top crust.

title: fresh vegetable marinade
directions: Wash, trim and cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite-sized pieces.
Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir well.
Add to vegetables, mixing well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: almond snack mix
directions: Place cereal and almonds in a large bowl; set aside. In a heavy saucepan, combine the sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until a candy thermometer reads 250° (hard-ball stage).

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Pour into lined 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° until set.
Top with meringue and brown meringue under broiler.

title: judy barton's salad
directions: Place pineapple in bowl.
Pour Jell-O over pineapple; mix and let sit for a few minutes.
Add low-fat cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Stir well.
This salad sets up immediately.
Refrigerate.

title: pickled okra
directions: Mix vinegar, water, and salt together and bring to a boil. Pack pint jars with okra. To each pint add: 1 clove, garlic, 1 pod hot pepper, 1 tbsp. dill seed. Pour hot mixture over and seal.

title: mocha walnut pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift first 7 ingredients together into a medium bowl.
Stir in walnuts.
In another bowl combine milk, butter, vanilla and rum.
Combine with flour mixture and mix until smooth.
Spread into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and sprinkle over top of batter mixture. Pour hot water over the top.
Do not mix.*
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool at least one hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: sea bass veracruzana
directions: Sprinkle the fish fillets on both sides with salt and pepper. Heat 1 very large or 2 medium size saute pans over medium-high heat for 1 minute.
Add the olive oil and when it is hot, but not smoking, add the fish fillets, skin side up.
Turn the heat to high and sear the fillets on the first side until golden brown, 1 to 2 minutes.
Turn and sear on the second side, 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Remove from the heat.

Using a slotted spatula, transfer the fillets to a rack set over a plate to catch the juices. Return the pan to high heat, add the onion and saute, stirring often, until lightly golden, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the garlic, jalapenos, lime wedges, tomato, oregano and olives and saute, stirring briskly for 1 minute longer.
Add the white wine and boil until reduced by half, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the fish stock or clam juice and bring to a boil.

Reduce the heat to medium-low and return the fish fillets, along with their juices to the pan. Cover and simmer gently until opaque throughout, 1 to 3 minutes, depending upon the thickness of the fillets.
Taste the broth and adjust the seasonings.
Using spatula, transfer the fish to warmed shallow soup bowls.
Ladle the broth into the bowls, arranging some of the vegetables from the broth on the top of each fillet. Serve immediately.

title: marshmallow crisp
directions: Melt butter in microwave in an 8-inch square baking dish (about 1 minute).
Add marshmallows, cover with plastic wrap and heat for 3 minutes; stir.
Add cereal, blend and press firmly into dish.
Yield: 16 bars.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Chop 1 large onion fine.
Use hot water barely enough to mix.
Add 2 eggs.
Drop by teaspoonful in hot oil until browned all over.

title: mexican layered bean dip
directions: In medium bowl mix together refried beans, chilies and taco seasoning mix.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Blend avocados, lemon juice and 1/2 cup taco sauce until smooth.
Spread on top of bean mixture.
Spread sour cream on top of avocado mixture.
Top with lettuce, onions, taco sauce, cheese and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: swiss meat balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine beef, 2 tablespoons onion soup mix and milk.
Mix well and shape firmly into balls.
Brown meat balls in butter.
Remove pan from heat.
Stir in flour, remaining soup mix, water and parsley.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Gradually stir in sour cream; heat, but do not boil. Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade baked beans
directions: Cover navy beans with cold water; soak overnight.
Drain. Cover with fresh water and simmer gently for 1 hour.
Add tomato soup, catsup, brown sugar, molasses, dry mustard and salt.
Place in skillet the bacon and onion.
Cook 5 minutes.
Put ingredients all together in a bean pot.
Bake at 250° for 6 hours.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix the cream cheese (softened), sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs.
Mix until blended.
Pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Top with fresh strawberries.
Cover with Marie's glaze for strawberries.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and smooth peanut butter.
This will be crumbly.
Line crust with this mixture, saving 2 tablespoons.
Mix vanilla instant pudding according to directions.
Pour over peanut butter mixture; sprinkle the 2 tablespoons of reserved mixture on top.
Refrigerate.
May use Cool Whip as topping.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Mix in the juices and freeze.
Remove 2 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale.
This will be slushy which is an ideal way to serve it.

title: kebapcheta(bulgarian meat sticks)
directions: Add salt to water. Wash the meat well. Chop into small cubes and pour over salted water. Wait about 10 minutes and mince meat with a meat mincer. Place in a dish or non-metal pan. Smooth it over and cover with a wet cloth. Place in refrigerator and leave overnight. The next day add pepper, allspice and comino. Let meat stand in refrigerator for 3-4 hours to become seasoned. Shape into sticks 5 inches long and 1 inch thick. Heat oil or lard in skillet over medium heat, cook until browned but still juicy, but not raw inside. Turn occasionally. Makes 10 servings.

title: date nut bread
directions: Let the first 3 ingredients cool.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake in a 325° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: brenda's apple pie
directions: Place apples in unbaked pie shell.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Add melted butter and last, add beaten egg.
Bake at 325° until brown.
Good to freeze, cooked or uncooked.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain off 1/2 the liquid from kidney beans, mixed beans and pork and beans.
Brown and drain bacon; cut small.
Brown and drain hamburger.
Put all the ingredients into a 6-quart crock-pot.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, onion, mustard, vinegar and butter beans.
Mix lightly
with large spoon.
Start cooking on high heat for one hour.
Mix again and be sure all ingredients are blended.
Cook on low heat for five hours.

title: milky way cake
directions: Combine Milky Way bars with 1/2 cup butter in a saucepan and melt over low heat.
While candy is melting, cream 1/2 cup butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and baking soda alternately with buttermilk.
Stir until smooth.
Add melted candy, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: quick fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix flour and other dry ingredients with 1 cup sugar and milk.
Stir until well blended. Pour the batter into the butter.
Add 3/4 cup sugar to fruit and heat.
Pour into batter.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: brenham earthquake cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
If you use foil pans, no need to grease them.
Spread coconut on bottom of pan.
Spread pecans on top of coconut.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour cake mix on top of pecans.
Mix softened margarine, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla. Drop spoonfuls of cheese mixture on top of cake batter; do not stir.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: teriyaki chicken(grilled)
directions: Put
chicken
breasts
in a gallon freezer bag.
Mix up marinade, enough to slightly cover the chicken.
Pour marinade on chicken
breasts
and
close
and turn the package several times to coat the chicken with the marinade.
Leave in refrigerator
for several
hours or overnight.
Turn several times. Remove
chicken from bag and save marinade.
Microwave chicken for at least 5 minutes.
Place chicken on grill and baste with the marinade, turning several times, until done.

title: granny's chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender; reserve the broth. After cooled, remove meat from bones. In large pot, put chicken broth, Veg-All, peas, soup, salt and pepper to taste. Add water if needed. Boil 5 to 10 minutes. Pour into 13 x 9 baking dish. Keep baking dish over the heat and let mixture continue to boil.

title: pecan kisses
directions: In bowl, beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form. Gradually beat in sugar, vinegar and vanilla.
Continue beating until very stiff.
Fold in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until firm. (Cookies should remain light colored.)
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen small cookies.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Dissolve jello in orange juice that has been heated.
Cool slightly. Pour in the cup of buttermilk and put in refrigerator until set.
Garnish with a dollop of mayonnaise.

title: mina moeckel's shortcake
directions: Work in butter with dry ingredients.
Mix to a soft dough with added milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until firm and done in the middle.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Arrange ingredients in a Pyrex casserole in this manner.
Lay in pork chops on the bottom, put onions, garlic and potatoes over them, then sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Now, pour the 2 cans tomato sauce over the top.
Refill cans with water and pour this over, also.
Bake in oven at 400° for 1 hour or more, until a fork goes through potatoes and meat easily.

title: milky way cake
directions: Combine candy bars and 1 stick butter in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Set aside.
Cream 2 cups sugar and 1 stick butter in a bowl, then beat in eggs.
Sift the flour with soda and add to the creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in candy mixture.
Add pecans and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured oblong baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Combine remaining sugar, milk and remaining butter in a saucepan and cook to soft ball stage, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Cool slightly.
Beat until thick and spread over cake.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

Mix the undrained pineapple and pie filling together. Dump the dry cake mix over top of fruit, spreading it out evenly. Slice oleo thinly and place on top of cake mix. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour until golden brown.
It will become crisp on top. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: makes own crust egg pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add to egg mixture.
Then add vanilla and milk.
Melt oleo in 9-inch pie pan.
Pour in mixture and bake until done (30 minutes at 350°).

title: cabbage salad
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar, oil, salt, celery seed and mustard over medium heat until dissolved.
Pour mixture over the shredded cabbage and onion; mix well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: home fries
directions: Mix oil and spices in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add potatoes and stir until coated. Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until lightly browned. Stir after 30 minutes.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Let stand for 30 minutes; drain.
Stir in flour and eggs.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot shortening in skillet.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Yields 6 servings.

title: garden salad
directions: Mix vegetables (all but cabbage).
Boil sugar, white vinegar, 1 teaspoon salt, celery seed and mustard seed; let cool.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon salt on shredded cabbage and let stand 1 hour. Squeeze out moisture.
Package and refrigerate what syrup you don't use for later date (does not call for oil).

title: venison roast
directions: Take a venison ham.
Slice several holes in the ham.
Plug each hole with a portion of a garlic clove, onion quarters and piece of green pepper.
This is best done by pushing the morsels in with the index finger.
Salt, pepper and garlic salt the ham.
(Try small sprinkle of red pepper or cayenne pepper if you dare.)
Place the ham in a baking bag.
Fill in around the ham with onions, carrots and potatoes.
Pour 2 cups of red wine over the venison ham and add flour.
Tie the bag.
Cook approximately 2 hours at 375°.

title: cocoon cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add vanilla and water.
Mix well.
Add flour; mix well.
Add pecans; mix well.
Form into small round balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 300° oven for about 30 minutes or until light brown on bottom.
Roll in powdered sugar while still hot.
Then roll 2 or 3 times more when cooled.

title: oven simmered beef brisket
directions: Trim and discard fat from meat.
Place brisket in roasting pan.
In bowl stir all ingredients but cornstarch and water. Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 3 hours.
Make gravy with cornstarch and water.

title: brunch sausage strata
directions: Line a greased 13 x 9-inch pan with bread slices.
Top each with a slice of cheese.
Spoon sausage over cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients together and pour over ingredients in pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Melt in double boiler. Add 2 cups chopped pecans; mix and drop by spoonfuls on buttered foil. When cool, drop in *Chocolate. Drain. Use toothpick.

title: chicken chestnut casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and lemon juice.
Add chicken, mushrooms, water chestnuts, onion and celery. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven and add egg slices.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese and French onion rings on top and bake for 15 more minutes.

title: sugar-free ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 1/2 gallon ice cream freezer; fill to freeze level with 2% milk and freeze.

title: plantano asado(columbian)
directions: In buttered mold, place alternate layers of plantain, cream and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts. Enjoy!!

title: my mom's great chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Work in shortening like a pie crust. Add milk. Work with hands until all ingredients are moist. Roll dough out onto floured surface to 1/4-inch thick. Slice into 2-inch squares.

title: spirited biscuits
directions: Toss dry ingredients to mix.
Cut in half the butter until the mixture resembles cornmeal.
Add whiskey and buttermilk and mix to form a dough.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half into a sheet 1/4-inch thick.
Cream remaining butter and spread on one sheet. Cover with second sheet.
Cut into rounds with biscuit cutter. Bake on ungreased baking sheet in a very hot oven at 500°, about 10 minutes.

title: my grandmother's rice pilaf
directions: Add rice to fat or butter.
Braise well until every kernel of rice is coated with fat or butter.
Pour boiling chicken broth over.
Season with salt and pepper and 1 tablespoon of grated onion.
Stir well.

title: b.b.q. country ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and boil for 5 minutes.
Roll ribs in flour & brown in oleo.
Put into a cooking bag.
Pour sauce over meat and bake 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 2 greased and floured bread pans. Sprinkle 2 teaspoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon over batter before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry yogurt dip
directions: Wash, hull and mash fresh strawberries.
Sprinkle sugar over them and let stand while preparing other ingredients.
Combine Cool Whip and yogurt, stirring together well.
Stir in strawberries. Chill until ready to serve.
Makes 5 cups.
Good served with all fruits.

title: canned pork
directions: Pack pork into	quart
canning	jars.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to each quart.
Pressure
for
minutes	at
10	to 15 pounds pressure.
Begin timing when pressure reaches 5 pounds. To serve, reheat contents.

title: chicken sauce piquant
directions: Cut up one large chicken (hen), 3 squirrels or 2 to 3 rabbits. Brown meat in cooking oil; remove.
Add flour and brown.
Add onions, celery, and bell peppers.
Cool until soft.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add meat and 1 quart of water. Cook until tender.
Season to taste.
Add onion tops and chopped parsley.

title: mrs. g's casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain the fat.
Add instant rice, corn, tomato sauce, water and salt and pepper to taste.
Place in casserole dish.
Lay strips of bacon across the top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hannah's favorite chicken and stuffing
directions: Place chicken in a deep baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Mix soup, sherry and milk together; pour over chicken and cheese.
Top with stuffing mix.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except apples and pecans, until well blended.
Then fold in apples and pecans.
Pour into Bundt pan, heavily coated with Crisco and flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: poppy seed tea bread(delicate, almond flavored pound cake, with crunchy poppy seed.)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, combine sugar, butter, eggs and extracts.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 12 cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 50 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely; sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: christmas aroma
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot and cover with water.
Bring to a boil. Let simmer all day adding water as needed.
Yields one fragrant home!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and zucchini.
Add dry ingredients. Blend in vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes in greased and floured loaf pans (2).

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler pan.
Meanwhile, mix coconut with syrup.
Squeeze into small balls.
Dip hands into cold water to erase stickiness after all balls are made.
Remove chocolate from stove (if completely melted).
Dip each ball into chocolate. Place each one on wax paper.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter-caramel cups
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and margarine and chill. Melt almond bark over double boiler.
Drop a bit of chocolate into decorative tins; put 1/2 teaspoon of peanut butter mixture or caramel and cover with more chocolate and refrigerate.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix to the consistency of pancake batter.
Cook on hot greased skillet, turning until both sides are brown.
Serve with butter or peanut butter and syrup.
Great side bread for dinner.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Cook the following ingredients until thickened:
dates, white sugar, water and chopped nuts.
Set aside while you cream shortening.
Add brown sugar.
Beat and add eggs.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to cream mixture.
Blend well.
Chill thoroughly. Then roll out in two rectangles 1/4 inch thick. Spread with the date filling and roll up like a Jelly Roll.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill overnight.

title: raspberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water or liquid from pineapple.
Add fruit and chill.

title: strawberry pie glaze
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick and clear (10 minutes).
Add strawberry jello.
Set aside until it cools. Pour over strawberries in pie shell.
Enough for 1 pie.

title: beets with pineapple
directions: Cook juice drained from beets and pineapple in saucepan with cornstarch, sugar and vinegar, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add salt and pepper to taste, drained beets and pineapple and butter.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes and serve hot or cold.
Serves 8.

title: ritzi broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese.
Mix well.
Add broccoli.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This may be prepared ahead of time and frozen until time to bake.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease large baking sheet. Sprinkle chicken lightly with salt and pepper to taste.
Stir together yogurt and mustard in a small bowl.
Spread mixture on bottom sides of chicken.
Place on baking sheet, coated side down, leaving space between pieces.
Spread mixture over top.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in butter in heavy pan.
Add onions; cook with meat for a minute.
Add salt and tomatoes.
Simmer while preparing other vegetables.
Add raw vegetables and cook until tender.
Use liquid from canned vegetables or water to cook vegetables in. Add remaining cooked vegetables and enough liquid for a soup and simmer 5 minutes.
Allow 15 minutes for rice.
Add before cooked vegetables.
Leave soup thick or add tomato or water.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine water, cloves and cinnamon.
Heat to boiling.
Add tea, cover and steep five minutes.
Strain.
Heat orange juice, lemon juice, and sugar to boiling; stir and add to hot tea.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chilies rellenos
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add chili powder and pepper. Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put a layer of split green chilies, cheese, meat, another layer of chilies, cheese and meat.
Mix eggs and sour cream.
Pour on top of meat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Pour sauce over and heat 5 minutes.
Serves 8 people. Good at brunch or supper.

title: crab pate
directions: Heat soup on low. Dissolve gelatin in cold water. Mix soup and gelatin together.
Mix next 5 ingredients together. Pour into a greased mold or bowl. Chill overnight.
Remove from mold.

title: jack straw carrots
directions: Wash and scrape carrots; cut lengthwise into thin strips.
Put Crisco in frying pan; add everything but milk.
Cover pan; let simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.
Turn frequently with spoon.
Drain off excess Crisco; pour milk into pan and stir well. Let get hot and serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: union pacific griddle cakes
directions: Break eggs into mixing bowl and beat well.
When well beaten, add the sugar or syrup and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in the milk and baking powder (which has been sifted into flour) and flour mixture.
Beat until smooth and then stir in butter last.
Do not beat after adding butter.
Batter should flow well when poured on griddle.
Cook on medium hot griddle.
Makes 1 quart of batter.

title: mexican corn stew
directions: Soak beans overnight in water to cover; drain and place beans in slow cooker.

title: mexican dip
directions: Heat in microwave slowly on 50% power or heat in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Use to dip with tortilla chips or potato chips.

title: johnny magetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain off water.
Brown hamburger and drain off grease.
Onion and olives are optional.
Pour in tomatoes. Add salt, pepper and oregano.
Let simmer.
Mix in with sauce and shredded cheese.

title: arlene's dill pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers from top down, leaving intact.
Fill jars with whole small cucumbers.
Put grape leaf and few green grapes in jar. Pour boiling water mixture into jars.
Seal.
Let set 6 months.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs until well blended.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Add nuts, carrots and vanilla; blend quickly.
Pour into well greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Best if let to set 1 day for easier slicing.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Top with grated Cheddar cheese and crumbled Ritz crackers. Melt one stick of margarine and pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all together and simmer 30 minutes.

title: quick venison stew
directions: Cook carrots after you peel and cube them.
Cut up celery and onion and saute in a little butter.
In a big pot, add potatoes, cooked carrots (use juice or water from both), canned venison and the sauteed onion and celery.
Add a little water if needed.
Mix 2 tablespoons cornstarch with a little water to make a paste.
Mix into pot gradually, stirring until it thickens slightly.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cracker crumbs and oleo.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle melted oleo over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut dessert
directions: To prepare crust, mix flour, sugar and butter; add nuts and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350° and then cool.

title: doris' nutritious muffins
directions: Stir together dry ingredients well, including sugar.
Mix applesauce, eggs, oil, raisins and nuts; stir into dry ingredients.
Mix only until blended.
Pour into lined muffin cups (fill 1/2 full) and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 30.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour, mixing well.
Add eggs, butter and buttermilk; beat well.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Prepare brownies following instructions.
Prepare mousse following instructions. Crush candy bars.

title: two-way pan cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy. Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture, blending thoroughly.
Stir in chocolate chips and peanut butter chips.
Spread batter into a greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely; cut in 20 bars.
Serve plain or topped with ice cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large pan.
Bring quickly to boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; stir until well mixed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: french fries - low-fat
directions: You will also need Pam spray (butter flavor).

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, melted butter, vanilla, milk, white sugar, eggs, crushed pineapple and coconut (if desired).
Spoon into greased casserole.
Mix flour, softened butter, pecans and brown sugar.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: barbecued ham
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients in a 3-quart casserole dish. Add ham and mix with sauce. Bake, covered, at 350° for at least 1 hour.

title: maple mustard ham steak
directions: Blend mustard, syrup and vinegar in small bowl; set aside. Grill or broil ham steak 3 minutes on each side.
Brush with 1/4 cup mustard mixture; cook 1 to 2 minutes more on each side.
Serve ham steak with remaining mustard mixture.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pour 1/3 cup melted butter over cubed bread.
Add chicken, soups and eggs and mix well.
Put into greased baking dish and top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mary's mock sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook carrots; drain well.
Blend in blender or food processor until fully blended.
Pour in bowl.
Do the same with the potatoes.
Add the next 8 ingredients to the carrots and potatoes and stir together well.
Pour in 9-inch pie shells.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and continue to cook for 15 more minutes.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: nutty chocolate chews
directions: In small bowl combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
In large bowl combine butter, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Add eggs, beat well.
Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips, 1/4 c. nuts, and lemon rind. Spread into greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 c.
nuts over top and press in.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: guava chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Add the 2 tablespoons sugar and lemon juice to thoroughly beaten egg yolks.
Cook on low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Blend in gelatin and remove from heat. Cool slightly before adding the guava nectar and coloring.

title: salad supreme
directions: Make lemon jello using pineapple juice as part of water necessary.
While hot, add marshmallows (cut small).
Set aside to cool and marshmallows dissolve.
Whip the cream; add salad dressing and cream cheese (cut into small pieces).
Add pineapple after lemon jello is cool.
Add whipped cream mixture and set aside to set.
When firm, make red jello and pour over the top.
Very beautiful and very delicious!

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Line 1 1/2-quart casserole with cooked broccoli.
Mix soup, margarine and curry.
Pour 1/2 over broccoli.
Cut cooked chicken into bite size pieces and place over soup mixture.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream together 1 cup grated sharp Cheddar cheese, 1 stick margarine and 1 cup flour.
Add 1 1/2 cups Rice Krispies and dash of red pepper.
Roll into small balls and press down with fork. Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: dad and sun saled dressing(a writing-to-read recipe)
directions: Shak well.
Let sit in frige for 10 minutes.
Eat and enjoy.

title: ez crock-pot chuck roast
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces.
Brown meat; put in crock-pot.
Add golden mushroom soup and dry onion soup.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
(The longer it cooks, the more tender it is.
Makes its own gravy.)

title: mustard salad dressing
directions: Beat until light and fluffy. Pour over cooked potatoes and stir to mix. Potatoes may be diced or sliced.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook fryer and remove from
bones.
Mix
chicken, soups and stock together and put in casserole
dish.	Bake
until it starts bubbling.	Add stuffing mix over
top
and
jam
down through other ingredients with knife.
Put	back
in
oven and bake for a few minutes at 350°.
Remove and serve.

title: crispy recipe
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Boil for 3 minutes and remove from heat.
Add Eagle Brand milk and boil 3 additional minutes.
Pour 1 large box Rice Krispies, puffed rice or popcorn into large bowl or roasting pan.
Pour cooked mixture over cereal and mix well.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour slowly.
Fold in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours in tube pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs until light and add mashed bananas thoroughly.
Add lemon juice.
Blend with creamed mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and mix quickly into banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Split batter into 2 bread pans and bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 4 tablespoons sugar and spread in oblong glass dish (12 x 8-inches).
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°, then cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread mixture over the crust and cover with favorite fruit.
Chill and serve.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Put sugar over berries and let stand for 1 hour; stir after 1 hour.
Combine water and Sure-Jell.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over berries; stir for 2 minutes.
Pour into jars up to 1/4-inch from top.
Put into freezer.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients
in
a	large
bowl; stir until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake	at
for 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted
in center comes out clean.
Spread with chocolate frosting.

title: company breakfast casserole
directions: Arrange bread slices in bottom of 8-inch pan; cover with cheese, ham and bread again.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings. Pour over bread and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until lightly browned and puffy.
Remove from oven and let stand for a few minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: corn dish
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn meal.
Add corn meal just as it is in the box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased Pyrex dish for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter straw pie
directions: Blend the peanut butter with the sifted powdered sugar until crumbly.
Sprinkle 2/3 cup of the mixture over a baked pie shell. Combine the flour, 1/2 cup sugar and the salt in saucepan.
Stir in the scalded milk.
Cook until thick.
Blend small amounts of mixture into 3 slightly beaten egg yolks.
Add to other mixture. Cook a few minutes longer.
Pour into pie shell.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown hamburg and
add
all other ingredients.
Cook 25 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: shrimp dip
directions: This is pretty straightforward.
Mix everything together; add Tabasco to taste. Can substitute the Tabasco with other hot sauces.
Single batch makes 4 cups; double makes 8 cups.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Slice onions thinly.
Saute in butter.
Layer in casserole dish: onions first, then crushed crackers.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, butter, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil quickly and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda; stir well.
Pour over popcorn in a large roasting pan and stir well.
Stir in peanuts, if desired.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes during baking.

title: oatmeal drop cookies(no baking required)
directions: In a saucepan, add the butter, sugar, milk and cocoa together. Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Cool slightly.
Drop teaspoonfuls of mixture onto wax paper; let cool completely.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: jane lusk's famous and secret chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
With a mixer, cream butters and sugars. Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
You may need to hand stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes (less time if your oven bakes hot).
Cookies should look slightly baked.
Do not brown! Let them sit on the cookie sheet for 5 minutes, then remove to a wire cooling rack.
Store in airtight container.
These cookies have a 2 to 3 day shelf life. You may want to freeze them in Ziploc bags.
They do freeze well, but once removed from the freezer, they have a 1 to 2 day shelf life.
You can double the recipe.

title: steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
In large skillet, brown meat in oil using high heat; add onions.
Saute until tender.
Blend soup, sherry (or water) and liquid from mushrooms.
Add to the meat and onions. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour or until steak is tender.
Or place in ovenproof casserole or pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pasta scampi
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
In large skillet, heat butter and oil. Add shrimp, shallots and garlic.
Cook 2 minutes; add remaining ingredients and cook until shrimp is pink.
Pour over pasta.

title: aloha cream pie
directions: In 9-inch pie pan, mix margarine and coconut.
Press firmly over bottom and up sides of pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes until edges are browned.

title: pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form dough into rope 8 inches long.
Let rise 15 minutes on aluminum foil-covered cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Mix 2 ingredients together until smooth. Divide into muffin cups. Bake at 350° for 18 to 21 minutes.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter in a bowl.
Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour with alternating milk, stir in extracts. Pour batter into greased and floured pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.

title: chicken soup...plus
directions: Place chicken in kettle.
Fill to nearly full with water.
Add a dash of salt and pepper.
Bring to boil then reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Remove chicken from broth to cool and skim fat from broth.
Measure broth and place in 10 quart pot; add enough water to make a total of 18 cups.
Add seasonings and fresh vegetables and boil.
Meanwhile, remove skin and bones from chicken and cut into small chunks.
Add frozen vegetables and chicken. Bring to boil again.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Remove bay leaves to serve.

title: festive fruitcake
directions: Spray
an
x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with nonstick spray coating.
In
a
medium
mixing bowl, combine fruit bits, raisins, pecans, maraschino cherries and vanilla.
Toss lightly. Drain pineapple well, reserving juice.
Set aside.

title: cousin janet's pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine flour, rolled oats, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter in mixing bowl.
Mix until crumbly using electric mixer on low speed.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Combine pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves in mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Pour into crust.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Combine nuts, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle over pumpkin filling. Return to oven and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool in pan on rack.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Makes 2 dozen.
Top with a dollop of cream if desired.

title: pumpkin pie dessert
directions: Combine Milnot and pumpkin in bowl; mix well.
Add sugar, eggs and cinnamon; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix; drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: emergency dressing
directions: Mix together in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until browned.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, about 4 hours. Before serving, arrange fruit on top.

title: egg souffle
directions: Oil 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Dip bread in butter to coat; do not soak.
Line Pyrex dish with bread.
Top with diced green chilies.
Layer cheese, black olives and ham on bread.
Separate 9 eggs.
Add half and half to egg yellows and beat.
Eat egg whites until stiff.
Fold yellow mixture into whites.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Can be mixed night before refrigerated and baked next morning.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 2 minutes or more.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until pie is firm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil all ingredients except peanut butter.
Stir constantly. Add 2 tablespoons peanut butter.
Stir until the mixture starts to set.
Pour into a buttered dish.

title: favorite macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line 2 cookie sheets with foil.
Mix together egg whites, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add flour and mix until well blended.
Fold in coconut.
Drop by teaspoons 1 inch apart on lined cookie sheets.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until light brown.
Cool on cookie sheet, then peel foil from cookies.
Makes about 28 cookies at 50 calories each.

title: three-onion relish
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add lemon juice and all onions.
Cook 10 minutes or until onions are crisp-tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Remove from heat; cool.
Cover and refrigerate at least overnight or up to 3 days for flavor to develop.
Serve at room temperature.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chocolate popsicles
directions: You will need eight 3 or 4 ounce paper cups and 8 popsicle sticks.

title: razorback chili
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Mix in chili, taco seasoning and jalapenos with hamburger and cook into meat.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer.
We put in crock-pot on low for a watch party.
The longer it slow cooks, the better it is.

title: christmas wreath
directions: Melt together butter, marshmallows and green food color (sufficient to make mixture a holly green color).
When melted and colored, add cornflakes to mixture and stir gently to thoroughly coat cereal with green mixture.

title: momma's red rice
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan.
Add tomatoes.
Add rice and stir.
Simmer for approximately 30 minutes or until rice is done. Crumble fried bacon on top of rice.

title: apple-spice upside-down cake
directions: Spread on well buttered glass baking dish, butter and brown sugar which have been mixed.
Arrange apple slices on top of this mixture.
Prepare your favorite spice cake mix according to directions on package.
Pour batter over apples and bake until cake is done.
Invert on serving plate and serve hot with lemon sauce or whipped cream.

title: chipotle pork posole
directions: Brown pork in olive oil. Drain; put in pot with onions, bell pepper, hominy, tomatoes, broth and salt. Bring to boil; reduce and cook on medium-low until meat is tender. Add chipotle peppers sparingly if you do not want it too hot.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Blend well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill for 4 hours.
Garnish with strawberries or pie filling.

title: curry sauce for chicken
directions: Cook onions gently in butter until glazed.
Add salt and curry powder.
Cook as long as you can without browning onions.
Add puree.
Bring to boil.
Cool to lukewarm.
Heat cream separately to same temperature as sauce.
Put sauce into cream by tablespoons. Don't boil!
This goes well with baked chicken, salad, rice and French bread.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and Crisco.
Stir until Crisco is dissolved and cool mixture to lukewarm.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in lukewarm water and egg.
Mix well . Stir in flour to make soft dough.
Rub surface with Crisco; cover tightly and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
(Will keep one week.) Place out and let rise in pans.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: crepes
directions: Add milk, flour and salt to eggs.
Mix until no lumps.
Pour from pitcher about 2 tablespoons of batter into pan.
Tip pan until bottom is coated (should be very thin).
Cook over low heat until crepe looks solid (about 30 seconds).
Turn and cook another 30 seconds.
Lightly grease pan about every third crepe.
Remove and cool on platter.
May stack.
Cover all with Saran and set aside.

title: tuna cheese spread
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature for 1 hour.
Drain tuna.
Mash with fork.
In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, tuna and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice, curry and salt.
Mix to blend well.
Add onions and stir to blend.
Chill for 1 hour for flavors to blend.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken tempters
directions: Combine chicken, celery and mayonnaise.
Add cream cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Make bite-size balls.
Roll in chopped pecans and refrigerate.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine the ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a greased and floured Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.

title: pineapple sandwich spread
directions: Mix together egg, flour, salt and sugar until smooth. Add pineapple. Cook over medium heat until thick. Remove from stove and let cool. Add mayonnaise and nuts. Store in refrigerator in airtight container.

title: party ryes
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix together sausage and hamburger.
Add seasonings and cheese, until all cheese is melted.
Let cool.
Spread on rye party bread. Freeze.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate 24 hours. Serve with raw carrots, celery, cauliflower, broccoli, green peppers or potato chips.

title: cherry topped cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix.
In large bowl, mix 1 egg, remaining cake mix and oil.
Press crust mixture evenly to bottom and 3/4 way up the sides of a pan.
In same bowl, blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add 3 eggs and reserved cake mix; beat 1 minute at medium speed.
At low speed, add milk and flavoring.
Mix until smooth.

title: 3-layer salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions on package.
Partial set.
Add 1 or 2 cans crushed pineapple (drain and save juice).

title: chocolate-peanut drops
directions: In large bowl stir together Frosted Flakes cereal and peanuts. Set aside.
Place peanut butter morsels and chocolate morsels in a microwavable bowl.
Heat on High 2 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking.
After cooking, stir morsels until smooth.
Pour melted morsels over cereal and peanuts, stirring until cereal and peanuts are coated.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet lined with waxed paper.
Chill until set, approximately 15 minutes.
Store at room temperature.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: green beans with feta and basil
directions: Steam beans until tender-crisp (approximately 4 minutes). Plunge in ice water. Drain. Whisk together mustard, vinegar, olive oil, salt and pepper in a large bowl. Add beans, Feta and basil; toss gently. Serves 12.

title: sugar cookie cut outs
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, milk and flavoring. Sift dry ingredients and add.
Roll out and cut and bake.
Makes about 60 cookies.
Bake at 350°.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into small balls (marble size).
Put on well greased baking sheet and bake in moderate oven (375°) until golden brown.
Let cool and then take up.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well, then add mashed bananas and vanilla.
Take some of the flour to flour nuts.
Sift dry ingredients and add with nuts to mixture.
Mix only enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Don't overmix.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake slowly in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: holiday cereal mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients.
Mix margarine and seasonings in double boiler (or over low heat).
Add first mixture; stirring well.
Bake in low oven at 250° for 2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: priscilla's chicken cordon bleu
directions: Halve chicken breasts; remove skin and bone.
Pound chicken thin; salt and pepper and cover each breast with a slice of ham and a slice of cheese.
Roll breasts and skewer with a toothpick.
Dip each in butter and then in bread crumbs.
Put in baking dish; pour remaining butter over chicken before baking.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add milk, salt, soda (optional) and cooking oil.
Add enough flour to clean sides of bowl; knead.
Have some flour on board and roll out fairly thin.
Let dry some and cut in strips, thin, 2 or 3 inch pieces.
Drop in hot broth.
Cook until tender.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill. Serve with fresh veggies.

title: diabetic fruit cake
directions: Pour orange juice and sweetener over chopped cranberries and let stand for 1 hour.
Combine raisins, pecans, pineapple, cranberries, orange juice, orange and lemon rind.
Add melted margarine.
Sift and measure flour.
Add salt, soda, allspice, cinnamon and nutmeg and sift again.
Add dry ingredients to fruit mixture and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Put 2 1/2 tablespoons of batter in each muffin cup.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, until lightly browned.
One muffin equals 1 serving.
Freezes well. Exchanges: 1 bread/1 fruit.
Makes 15 to 18 cupcakes.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of mixer until creamy.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt, soda and mix into creamed mixture until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar. Add pumpkin, spices, flour and milk. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes. Turn oven to 350 degrees and bake an additional 40 minutes. Makes 2 shallow 9 inch pies or 1 9 inch deep dish pie.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon in bowl.
Melt and bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa and water.
Add to flour and sugar mixture.
Beat well.
Add buttermilk and baking soda.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Bake in 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate and roll into a ball. Freeze and dip in chocolate chips.
If desired, melt chocolate chips in double boiler and use to dip Peanut Butter Balls in. Place on waxed paper until chocolate cools and sets.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat the eggs slightly.
Add the other ingredients and mix well.
Pour this into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake until firm. Yield: 6 servings.
