title: eggplant italiano
directions: Pare eggplant and slice 1/8-inch thick.
Spread 2 tablespoons tomato sauce in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Layer half of eggplant, 1 can tomato sauce, half of oregano and half of sharp cheese.
Repeat layers; cover dish.
Place in microwave and cook 14 to 16 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese and continue to cook 1 to 2 minutes until cheese has melted.

title: glazed fruit dessert
directions: In mixing bowl, combine pudding and pineapple juice.
Stir until thickened.
Fold in pineapple, oranges and bananas. Refrigerate until serving time.
Top each serving with a spoon of Cool Whip.
Garnish with a cherry.

title: pork stir-fry
directions: Cut pork into 1/4-inch strips.
Slice broccoli stalks into thin rounds, about 1/8-inch thick.
Break broccoli head into small flowerets.
Cut carrots in half crosswise; then cut into thin strips, about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut onion in thin strips, about 1/4-inch thick.
Heat oil and garlic in wok or skillet.
Add pork and broccoli stems; cook, stirring constantly, over high heat until pork is no longer pink.
Add carrots, onion and flowerets. Reduce heat, cook, covered, 5 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour into skillet.
Simmer for 2 minutes until sauce is thick.
Serve over rice, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops; place in casserole dish.
Spread mushroom soup over pork chops; add uncooked rice.
Add tomatoes, including liquid and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ola's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast into water.
Put everything into a bowl and stir until just mixed.
Be careful not to overmix.
Cover and let rise to double its size.
Stir in down and cover and put in the refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.
Two hours before baking time, grease baking pan.
Dust dough with flour until it can be rolled out onto a board.
Roll dough, cut and place on pan. Grease tops with melted butter.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Bake in 425° oven until brown.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat until well done.
Drain off any fat.
Add 2 cans enchilada sauce and a little water from each can (rinse them out). Heat tortillas in microwave until soft.
Spoon meat/sauce mixture in center of each tortilla.
Sprinkle with both cheeses.
Roll up and place edge side down in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
The pan should hold 8 to 10 rolled enchiladas.
Spoon remaining sauce over enchiladas and sprinkle with remaining cheeses.
Bake at 325° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: mexican meatballs
directions: Mix ground turkey, crumbs, onion, horseradish, Tabasco, eggs, salt and pepper.
Form meat mixture into 3/4-inch meatballs and cook until browned.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken on all sides in oil, about 10 to 15 minutes. Add onion and garlic; add oregano and tomato sauce.
Cover pan tightly and simmer about 30 minutes, then add wine or vinegar wine; add parsley, mushrooms and rest of seasonings.
Cook 15 minutes more with cover on.

title: absolutely easy yogurt bread
directions: 1. In a large bowl mix water, dry yeast, and honey or sugar. Stir to dissolve and let sit for 5 minutes. 2. Add salt and plain yogurt.
Mix throughly. 3. Using heavy spoon stir in about 7 1/2 c. flour until the dough starts to leave sides of bowl.
Knead on floured surface for 5-10 minutes until dough starts to feel satiny and pops back when you poke it. 4. Cut in half.
Shape loaves and put into pans sprayed with pam.
Cover and let rise in warm spot until dough rises to top of pan (about 30 minutes). 5. Bake in preheated oven for 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove immediately to cool on wire rack.

title: apricot bars
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, butter, 1 egg and milk.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan (moisten hands with water while patting).
Spread apricot jam over this.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook and then drain frozen broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in greased dish at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Beat in syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes or until done.

title: cheese olive potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes and put in 1 large dish.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Stir in flour.
Add milk.
Add Worcestershire and dry mustard.
Add American cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add olives.
Pour over potatoes and sprinkle with paprika.

title: miniature ham and cheese rolls
directions: Do not break rolls apart -- but, slice lengthwise through center.
Layer ham and cheese between sliced rolls.
Replace top rolls and put rolls back in foil tray.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over rolls.
Leave uncovered until butter sets, then cover with foil.
Bake covered for 13 minutes at 350°.
Yields:

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix together in large bowl all main ingredients.
Then in small bowl mix together dressing ingredients and pour over main ingredients.
Toss and cover.
Allow to chill.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Scrub and bake potatoes. Cut in half and scoop out pulp. Discard skins.

title: maple syrup
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Cover; cook 1 minute. Cool slightly.
Add the vanilla and maple flavoring.
Cover saucepan for a few minutes as syrup cooks to melt down crystals. This helps syrup from crystallizing later in storage.

title: rice-a-roni hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add Rice-A-Roni and prepare according to the package directions.
When 5 minutes are left, add corn.
Quick, easy and tasty.

title: beet pickles
directions: Simmer 15 minutes. Add to beets. Pack in jar.
Water bath 5 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Place carrots in Pyrex dish. Slice the onion and green pepper. Put on top of carrots. Mix together remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour this over carrots, onion and bell peppers. Chill overnight before serving.

title: chicken with 40 cloves of garlic
directions: Cut the chicken into serving pieces.
Rinse and pat dry. Season with salt and pepper.
In a large casserole with a tight-fitting lid, heat the oil and brown the chicken in it.
When browned, drain the fat from the pan.
Add the garlic, parsley, thyme or tarragon and wine or broth.
Cover the pan with foil, then place the lid firmly on top.
Cook over very low heat for 2 hours.
The chicken and garlic should be completely tender.
Serve with country bread.
Dip bread into the juices from the chicken. Roasted garlic may be squeezed on the bread for an added treat.

title: mom's cookies
directions: In bowl, mix all ingredients.
Spoon drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: slush
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in container in freezer. Five-quart ice cream pail works well.
Remove from freezer and serve with sweet or sour soda.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and Crisco by hand until crumbly.
Take out 1 cup for top, then add boiling water, molasses and baking soda.
Mix together. Put into greased pan.
Put crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Mix chicken soup, salsa, sour cream, green onions and 2/3 cup cheese. Add chicken. Put 2 to 3 teaspoons mixture in each tortilla. Roll up and place in a greased casserole dish, seam side down. Pour any leftover mixture on top of tortillas, then cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, milk and egg to make a batter.
Slice tomatoes 3/8 inch thick.
In a large skillet heat bacon drippings (1/4 inch deep).
Sprinkle tomato slices with salt and pepper. Coat tomato slices
in self rising flour, dip in batter, dip again in flour and again in batter.
Fry in bacon drippings until golden brown, turning once, remove from skillet and drain on paper towels.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook in crock pot 6 to 8 hours or until it reaches the consistency you want.
Stir periodically.

title: wheat muffins
directions: Beat
together milk, egg and butter; add this to flour, baking powder, salt and sugar mixture.
Put in muffin tins and bake
until
golden
brown.
Pat butter on top after baking.

title: peanut butter fudge(easy-no testing)
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in pan and cook at 280°.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until well blended and pour into 8-inch pan.
Allow to cool and cut into squares.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Make gelatin
with 1 cup hot water, juice from a can of crushed pineapple
and
vinegar.
(If there is not a cupful of juice,
finish
with
water.)
When gelatin begins to congeal, combine other ingredients with it.
Serves 6.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese. Put 1/2 of mixture into a pan. Add cheese. Pour rest of mixture over cheese. Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2 quart casserole; mix all ingredients except 2/3 c. French fried onions. Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees or until hot. Stir; top with 2/3 cup French fried onions. Bake for 5 minutes longer, or until onions are golden brown.

title: super crabmeat dip
directions: Drain and remove cartilage pieces from crabmeat.
Combine other ingredients. Cover and chill.

title: cheddar potatoes
directions: Spread hash browns on the bottom of baking dish so they cover the entire bottom of the baking dish.
Spread soup evenly on top of hash browns.
Add onion and seasoning.
Cover with layer of sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve hot!

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat the butter and sugar to a cream.
Add the coconut and eggs.
Then add the milk and sift flour and baking powder.
Flavor to taste.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well until creamy.
Bake in three 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream of tartar cookies
directions: Sift flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Add sugar.
Mix in Crisco until fine (like corn meal).
Add enough egg to hold together.
Roll out about 1/8-inch and cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 425° until lightly golden, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin and white chocolate cookies
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon, cardamon and baking soda in a small bowl.
Beat butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar in large mixing bowl until creamy.
Beat pumpkin, egg and vanilla; beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in chips and nuts.

title: strawberry cream in swiss meringues
directions: Combine the strawberries, 1/4 cup of the sugar and salt.
Whip the cream until almost stiff.
Beat in remaining sugar gradually, then add the vanilla.
Fold in the strawberries and chill.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.

title: peppermint float
directions: Combine candy, 1 pint softened ice cream and milk in large mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer until slushy. Pour into chilled glasses; top each glass with a scoop of ice cream.
Garnish with crushed candy, if desired.

title: **heavenly salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cheese and beat until dissolved.
Chill slightly.
Add pineapple and nuts.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, chicken soup and half of the onions, crumbled.
Pour into baking dish.
Place the rest of the onion rings on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: green salad unique with poppy seed dressing
directions: Tear lettuce and spinach into bite-size pieces.
Add remaining salad ingredients.
For dressing, combine all ingredients in covered jar and shake well.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Just before serving, toss salad with dressing.
Makes 20 servings.
(I cut this down for smaller groups.)

title: easy 7-layer dip
directions: In serving dish, layer the following ingredients in order: bean dip, guacamole, sour cream, tomatoes, olives, cheese and green onion and chill.
Serve with Fritos corn chips scoops.

title: no crust custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, sugar and salt.
Mix well and pour into pie tin that is greased with 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° in glass pie pan for 30 to 40 minutes (350° for tin pan).
Pie tests done when knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Boil tomatoes until soft, strain.
Cook onions and hot peppers in 2 cups oil until onions are soft.
Add rest of ingredients with tomatoes and cook 3 hours.
Then add tomato paste.
Bring to boil and pour into jars or freeze in containers enough for serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together well.
Put teaspoons of dough on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Watch because ovens vary.

title: fried cheese balls
directions: Heat 2 inches of oil in small fryer or small saucepan.
Beat 1 cup Bisquick mix, milk and egg by hand until smooth.
Insert toothpick into cheese cube, then coat cheese lightly with dry Bisquick mix, dipping into batter to cover completely.
Fry several cheese balls at a time until brown.

title: cream cheese delights
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together margarine, cake mix and 3/4 cup of pecans.
Pat out evenly in bottom of pan.
Mix together cream cheese and brown sugar and spread on top of cake layer.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Use glass bowl.
Place spinach in layer in bowl.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Top with sliced eggs, then bacon, lettuce, more salt, pepper and sugar.
Add onions and uncooked frozen peas.
Repeat this process until bowl is full.
Mix mayonnaise and Miracle Whip and spread over salad, sealing edges. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Wash and cut zucchini.
Peel and slice onions.
Place in crock or bowl with salt.
Cover with water; let stand 1 hour.
Drain. Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over zucchini and onions.
Let stand another hour.
Bring to another boil for 3 minutes.
Pack in jars; seal, processing for 10 minutes.

title: stained glass cookies
directions: Melt chips and margarine/butter in double boiler or heavy pan. Let cool. Add nuts and marshmallows; mix well. Separate into 3 logs using wax paper. This part is messy! Sprinkle coconut on wax paper and roll each log in coconut. Wrap each log in wax paper, then foil and freeze. When you are ready to serve, slice cookies 3/8 to 1/2-inch thick.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook first three ingredients until soft ball stage.
Add peanuts and cook until hard crack stage (300°).
Then add soda and pour on marble slab.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent roll dough flat on a cookie sheet (ungreased) stretching out to edges of pan.
Bake as directed on pkg. until golden brown. As pastry cools combine cream cheese, ranch dressing and mayonnaise.
Mix well then spread over crust.
Sprinkle veggies over cream cheese (except tomatoes).
Then put grated cheese over all and press down and last add tomatoes.
(Veggies will fall off if not pressed into cream cheese and tomatoes get soggy if not added just before serving.)
I cut mine in squares to serve but it can be cut in wedges
like pizza.
Crust and cream cheese layer can be prepared ahead and tightly covered and chilled and veggies added later.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in oleo.
Add broccoli, milk, soup, water, rice and salt.
Mix all well and put in casserole.
Cover with cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chip dip
directions: Cut onion in chunks.
Put in blender.
Add milk and blend. Pour 2 drops of ketchup to color, 6 shakes of Tabasco, salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 teaspoon of garlic salt in the blender. Add cream cheese (cut in cubes) and blend.

title: sand tarts(the christmas cookie)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Cream butter and beat in sugar.
Add beaten eggs alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Form into rolls.
Chill or freeze.
Slice very thin with wet knife.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar (and colored sprinkles if desired).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter together.
Add rest of ingredients. Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: quick crepes
directions: Mix the commercial pancake mix in a large bowl, using 1/4 to 1/8 cup more liquid than called for in the instructions.
Grease a large cast-iron frypan with margarine or butter and set on medium heat.
Ladle or spoon 1 large pancake onto the heated pan.
As the cake sets (bubbles break), sprinkle 1 teaspoon of sugar onto the uncooked side.
Turn.
Place 1 to 2 teaspoons of fruit filling onto 1/2 the cooked side.
Wait 10 seconds.
Fold.
Turn twice.
Serve.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer at least 1 hour.
Note: This is like stew in that it gets better the next day.
Also you can add potatoes, rice or pearl barley.

title: ginger creams(cookies)
directions: Cream sugar, water, molasses, shortening and egg.
In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients together.
Combine all above ingredients.
Drop by spoon onto baking sheet.
Bake for approximately 10 minutes at 400°.
Top with your favorite frosting or icing.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix the cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup of sugar and the margarine into a bowl; set aside until later.
Mix the Dream Whip according to directions in another bowl.
Add the cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar to the Dream Whip; mix well.
Put 1/2 of the cracker crumb mix in the bottom of a bowl or casserole dish. Put 1/2 of the Dream Whip mix over the crumb mix, then the can of cherry pie filling over the Dream Whip mix.
Put the remaining Dream Whip mix, then the remaining cracker crumbs. Refrigerate until set.

title: double cheese macaroni
directions: Cook and drain rigatoni.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in large saucepan.
Add olives, tomato pieces, 1/4 cup parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix together and pour over the macaroni.
Toss lightly and place in a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Mix cottage cheese, sour cream, milk and chili sauce together and pour over macaroni mixture.
Saute bread crumbs and walnuts in remaining butter until golden brown.
Sprinkle crumbs, nuts, the rest of the parsley and the Gouda cheese on the casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken slowly with carrots, Vidalia onion and seasoning; drain.
Remove chicken and cool; chop and set aside.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
In 3-quart or more soup kettle, place all ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Simmer, covered, for at least an hour.
Longer cooking blends flavors more.
Hearty and delicious!

title: "most excellent brownie cookies"
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare an ungreased cookie sheet with aluminum foil on flat surface.
Beat shortening, brown sugar, water and vanilla until well blended.
Add eggs, beat well.
Stir flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda together.
Add to egg-sugar mixture, beat until well blended.
It will be stiff.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon 2-inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until set.
Cookies will appear soft and moist.
Do not overcook.
Cool 2 minutes, place on foil to cool.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Melt butter in a pan; blend in flour and add cream all at once. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir about half the hot mixture into egg yolks; return to hot mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened, but do not boil.
Add lobster; heat through.
Stir in wine, lemon juice and salt.
Sprinkle with paprika; spoon into patty shells.
Serves 4.

title: silver white cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add shortening, 2/3 cup milk and flavoring.
Beat well.
Add rest of milk and stiffly beaten egg whites.
Beat well.
Bake at 350°.

title: fat-free salad dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a blender; process until mixed thoroughly.
Serve on your favorite salad.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate chip cookies at their best
directions: In large bowl of an electric mixer, beat butter, shortening, granulated sugar and brown sugar on high speed until very light and fluffy (about 5 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla and lemon juice.
In another bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and oats.
Gradually add to butter mixture, blending thoroughly.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Use a scant 1/4 cup of dough for each cookie.
Drop dough onto lightly greased baking sheets, spacing cookies about 3 inches apart.
For soft cookies, bake in 325° oven for 17 to 19 minutes or until light golden brown.
For crisp cookies, bake in 350° oven for 16 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Transfer to racks and let cool.
Store airtight. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: slush mix
directions: Boil together water and 1 cup sugar.
Boil separately 2 cups of water and 2 green tea bags. Let cool.
Add lemonade, lime and gin.
Mix together and put in ice cream pail.
Freeze several hours.
Serve diluted with
a little club soda or sour mix.

title: easy stew
directions: Cover potatoes and onion with water and boil until tender. Brown meat; drain.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and beans to meat mixture.
Add to potatoes.
Additional water may be added, if needed.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with hot cornbread or crackers, if you prefer.

title: caramel pecan rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, shortening, salt, egg and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add additional flour until dough is easy to handle.
Place in greased bowl, turn to grease top, and cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight or up to 5 days.
Combine margarine, brown sugar and corn syrup.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 15 x 9-inch rectangle. Spread with melted margarine and sprinkle with sugar mixture. Beginning at long edge, roll up tightly.
Cut into 1-inch slices and place in prepared pan.
Let rise, covered, in warm place (85°) until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert on baking sheet.
Serve warm.
Yield: 18 rolls.

title: sausage delight
directions: Unroll one can of rolls.
Place square sections side by side on cookie sheet, pressing seams together.
Spread cooked, crumbled sausage on top of rolls.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Unroll other can of rolls.
On waxed paper, spread each square section and gently press dough out and press seams together.
Gently lay first square over top of sausage/cheese.
Repeat other section of dough and press top section of dough to bottom and press top seams together.
Bake in oven at 350° until rolls are brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: black-eyed pea salsa
directions: Drain peas in colander.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in black-eyed peas.
Serve on lettuce leaf with tortilla chips.

title: pink fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cheese in small pieces. Add cherries and pineapple.
Set until partly jelled.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add chopped walnuts.
May freeze.
Cut and serve while partially frozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish. Bake about 1 hour and 25 minutes at 225°.
Stir frequently.

title: yogurt pops
directions: Mix until well blended.
Pour into small paper cups.
Insert popsicle stick in center and freeze.
Makes 10 to 15 pops.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Combine oil, butter and mini marshmallows.
Melt on low heat until marshmallows are melted.
Pour over popcorn mixing with a large spoon.
Put gumdrops and nuts in greased angel food pan. Press popcorn mixture on top.
Remove from pan by running a knife around the edge.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Stir well.
Add flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Stir well.
Pour in a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: horseradish carrots
directions: Scrub and slice carrots (diagonally).
Cook.
Drain and save liquid.
Mix together onion, horseradish, mayonnaise, salt and pepper and the liquid.
Put carrots in casserole; add the mixture over top of carrots.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Add small amount of melted butter to bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Combine bell pepper, onions, celery, rice, hard egg white and chicken.
Blend bouillon cubes in mayonnaise.
Add to rice-chicken mixture.
Season to taste and toss slightly.
Spoon into a Pam sprayed 2-quart casserole.
Top with crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Form into ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Chill thoroughly.

title: poor boy stew
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off excess grease.
Peel, slice and cook onion and potatoes until tender.
Add just enough water to boil.
Add the cooked hamburger, peas and milk.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: angel food-pineapple cake
directions: Cook pineapple in its own juice.
Add pudding to boiling juice of pineapple.
Remove from stove and stir.
Let sit until cools. Use mixture to ice angel food cake.

title: amish cinnamon bread
directions: Mix ingredients together by hand; do not use a mixer.
Add 1 cup each nuts or fruits.
Bake in two loaf pans in a 325° oven for one hour.
Spray loaf pans with Pam so bread can be removed easily.
This can also be baked in a Bundt pan.

title: dog biscuits(make your own)
directions: Mix flour, oats and beaten eggs.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water.
Add to mixture with rest of ingredients (cold water, soy or Worcestershire sauce).
Mix well (rather stiff).
Drop in any size or shape you like on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.
Watch not to burn.
Turn off oven and leave in oven another 1 hour.
Don't package until completely cooled.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over Shredded Wheat and raisins. Let stand until cool. Cream the oleo and sugar. Add Shredded Wheat, raisins and egg.
Mix well.
Slowly sift flour (with baking soda added). Alternate with buttermilk, add to mix.
Add All-Bran mixed with cinnamon.
Mix and store in refrigerator. Do not mix after batter is stored.
Spoon as needed into greased muffin pans. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until done. Batter improves with age. Can be kept 6 weeks.
Serve with cream cheese or butter.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Combine cookies and melted butter.
Freeze for 20 minutes. Melt marshmallows; add milk.
Cool this mixture.
Whip the whipping cream; add to mixture creme de cacao and creme de menthe.
Pour into pie shell.
Shave chocolate over top.
Let set overnight before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat well, sugar, eggs and oil.
Add flour, soda, salt, baking powder, nuts, cinnamon, zucchini and vanilla.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Insert a toothpick; turn out at once.
Slice and spread with Philadelphia cream cheese.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown together Hamburger & Taco Seasoning
Mix. Mix with other ingredients.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Keep in a covered jar.
Use to suit taste, a cup or a pot at a time.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brush chicken with melted butter.
Roll in mixture of bread crumbs and spices.
Arrange crumb coated chicken breast, skin side up on foil lined cookie sheet.
Do not overlap pieces.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Brush chicken generously with mayonnaise.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake 1 hour or until chicken is tender and well done.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Work shortening until creamy.
Stir in sugar gradually.
Add egg and beat well.
Add sour cream.
Mix well.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Roll and cut with cookie cutters. Brush cookies with egg whites.
Add sprinkles before baking.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: italian cookies
directions: Beat eggs with an electric mixer until thick and lemon colored. Add oil gradually, then sugar, milk, vanilla and anise oil.
Beat 5 minutes longer.
Sift together dry ingredients; gradually beat into egg mixture.
Turn out on floured pastry cloth; knead dough until smooth.
Roll out and cut strips about 2 inches long and 1 inch wide.
Tie each strip into a knot.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until delicately browned.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: double chocolate layer bars
directions: Combine cake mix, oleo and egg.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle coconut, then chocolate chips and nuts. Cover with milk.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool before cutting.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Put popped corn in a large paper grocery bag.
Pour boiled mixture over the popped corn.
Fold bag over and shake.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Remove and shake.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Remove and shake.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Remove and shake.
Pour into a large container and let cool.

title: tuna-mac salad
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with vegetable and hot rolls.

title: soft tacos
directions: Place 1 can rolls in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown hamburger (pour off grease).
Add taco seasoning and water; simmer.
Spread on crescent roll layer.
Layer with slices of American cheese.
Place another can of rolls on top.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, butter and eggs.
Alternate flour and oil until mixed.
Chill for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Dip bottom of glass in sugar and press.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Dough keeps up for 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: banana salad
directions: Slice bananas.
Mix eggs, milk and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until mixture curdles.
Add peanut butter. Pour over fresh cut bananas, mix well.

title: tiny pecan pies
directions: Beat together until smooth, all except pecans.
Divide half of the pecans among pastry-lined cups; add filling.
Top with the remaining pecans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until set.
Cool and remove from pans.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: easy red chili
directions: Brown hamburger in an eight quart pot.
Drain fat.
Add kidney beans (undrained), tomato sauce, packages of chili seasoning mix, 1/2 package of taco seasoning mix and water.
Mix thoroughly.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer, cover, and cook for 30 - 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: cereal party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt margarine in shallow baking pan.
Stir in salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to coat pieces with margarine.
Heat 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool.
Store in tight container.
Makes eight 1/2-cup servings. 92 calories; 4 grams fat; 203 mg. sodium per 1/2 cup serving.

title: pickled eggs and red beets(penna. dutch for picnics, salad or brown bag)
directions: Wash beets, cut off leaves and stems, leaving about 1 inch of the root end.
Cook until tender.
Drain and skin.
(You can use canned beets, sliced if fresh are not available.)
Fresh beets make a lot of stain mess.
Combine brown sugar, vinegar, water, salt, cinnamon stick and cloves; bring to boil.
Cook 10 minutes.
Let beets stand in their liquid for several days.
Shell eggs, place whole in beets; let stand in refrigerator at least 2 days.

title: raspberry carasel salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cranberry juice cocktail.
Chill until thickened, about 1 hour. Fold in apple, celery and walnuts.
Spoon into 6-cup ring mold and chill until set, about 15 minutes.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened, about 45 minutes.
Combine Cool Whip and mayonnaise.
Fold into lemon gelatin.
Spoon into mold and chill until firm.

title: chicken soup meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients; shape into loaf.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Cover lightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.
If desired, uncover last 15 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in blender and let stand in refrigerator to blend flavors.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix all together.
Marinate 24 hours with beef, chicken or pork.
Grill on a barbecue or gas grill.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly margarine, shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Blend in flour.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon. Roll balls in mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: mamaw henry's chili con carne
directions: Brown beef and add
other ingredients.	Cook slowly for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13 pan, dump pineapple and spread evenly. Spread cherry pie filling over pineapple. Sprinkle dry cake mix over cherries. Add nuts. Slice margarine and dot on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cauliflower cream soup
directions: Cut cauliflower in bite size pieces.
Combine with water, onion and butter in 2-quart glass casserole dish.
Cover with lid. Microwave on High for 5 to 10 minutes.
Combine flour, salt and cream; mix well.
Stir into vegetables; cover and microwave on High until it boils or thickens.
Stir in cheese and mustard. Microwave on High, uncovered, 2 or 3 minutes, until cheese melts. Stir once.
Can freeze half if you want.
Keeps up to 3 months. Makes 10 servings.
Other vegetables can be used, if desired (broccoli, carrots or zucchini).

title: orange cookies
directions: Cut orange candy into small pieces into a bowl.
Add cup flour over pecans and candy.
Beat your eggs real good; add sugar, butter, cake flour and vanilla.
Then add flour and baking soda, then coconut, nuts and candy.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until light brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and roll into a ball.
Roll in finely chopped pecans. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding and sugar. Add oil and water and stir. Beat in eggs, one at a time, with a wooden spoon. Add sour cream and chips. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in a greased and floured Bundt pan. Cool one hour before removing from pan. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Enjoy!!

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together.
Roll in balls.
Freeze or chill thoroughly. Dunk in chocolate.
(Heat chocolate chips and paraffin over hot water to dunk.)

title: chocklet chep cuckies
directions: Roll dowe pot on ches.
And then pprrone on it and then metbolls and coke and then you have pizza.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Combine all in a crock pot.
Cook on high until melted; turn to low for serving.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: In double boiler, beat eggs and milk.
Add sugar and salt. Stir and cook constantly over hot water until thick enough to coat a metal spoon.
Let cool, then add cream and vanilla.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: leg of lamb with garlic
directions: Remove meat from refrigerator 3 to 5 hours before cooking. Insert pieces of garlic all around the leg by making tiny incisions and pushing garlic in.
Season meat with salt and pepper.
Pour a little vegetable oil over meat and let marinate until cooking time.
Simmer brown stock with sherry until reduced by half.
Place leg in roasting pan in preheated 450° oven, leave door ajar, turn frequently and baste with oil.
When outside is crisp (about 45 minutes), take meat out of pan and place in fresh pan.
Roast the potatoes in first pan for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Reduce temperature to 300°.
Place lamb in oven.
Baste with stock and sherry frequently.
Roasting time is 20 minutes per pound, less 45 minutes.
Serve with lima beans and roasted potatoes.

title: peach dessert
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with water.
Add pudding and whisk until thick.
Add 1/2 (8 ounce) carton Cool Whip.
In a casserole dish layer cake, pudding and peaches.
Repeat.
Refrigerate until set. Top with remaining Cool Whip.
It is so good!!

title: spinach casserole
directions: Boil
fresh
green
beans
in salted water until bright green. After
boiling,
toss in hot skillet to evaporate extra moisture. Toss
again with lemon juice and butter.
Serve and enjoy.

title: speedy apple crisp for one
directions: In a small glass pie plate, combine the first 4 ingredients. Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Turn dish and cook 2 more minutes.
Sprinkle with granola or Grape Nuts before eating.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Stir in egg.
Add vanilla and water. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Drop by half teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: pasta primavera salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, adding vegetables to water during last 5 minutes of cooking.
Drain; rinse with cold water and drain again.
Place in large serving bowl; toss with salad oil.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Mix all together; fry until meat is brown and simmer 15 minutes. Serve on buns.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Add beef and onion.
Cook until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat. Sprinkle in seasonings and flour.
Stir well.
Gradually add Carnation milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Gradually add catsup.
Heat to serving temperature. Serve on buns.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add thawed strawberries and pineapple with juice.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into 8 x 8-inch serving dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Let remainder stand at room temperature.
After jello in refrigerator is firm, spread pint of sour cream over jello and sprinkle with nuts.
Pour remaining jello mixture over top and refrigerate until firm. Slice and serve on dessert or salad dishes.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Place half of the ham in bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish. Cover with half of the potatoes and half of the onion. Sprinkle half of the flour and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat layering of ham, potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle with additional salt and pepper. Sift remaining flour on top.
Pour milk over all. Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours until potatoes are nearly tender.
Uncover. Combine bread crumbs and melted butter. Sprinkle on casserole. Bake 15 minutes more.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Cover with crushed corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chile con queso
directions: Heat all ingredients over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.

title: dressing for melon balls
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Cook until thick (double boiler).
Cool.
Add 1/2 pint whipped cream or Cool Whip.
If not thick enough, add more flour.
